(70, 'Buddha Purnima (H): May 5', 'Worldwide', '5', '5', '2023', '2023-05-05', '5', '5', '2023', '2023-05-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '38', '13', '70', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.indif.com/nri/festivals/buddha_poornima.asp', '9071_Buddha_PurnimaF.jpg', '9071_Buddha_PurnimaE.jpg', 'About the Hindu day of Buddha Purnima', NULL, 'Buddha Purnima is an important day for Buddhists and Hindus. This holiday commemorates the birth, enlightenment and death  of Gautama Buddha and always falls on the falls full moon night in the month of Vaisakha of the Hindu calendar.  In the Gregorian calendar, this occurs in April or May. \n\nLord Buddha was the founder of the Buddhist religion and is said to be the ninth avatar of Vishnu. \n\nThe main celebrations of Buddha jayanti take place in Bodh Gaya (Bihar, India). \n\nBodh Gaya is the most sacred place for Buddhists. \n\nTemples are decorated and prayers, sermons and non-stop recitations of Buddhist scriptures resonate in monasteries, religious halls and homes.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: \nWe use the Indian Civil Calendar, which is the official holiday calendar in India, the largest Hindu nation.  The Hindu faith has many calendars, each specific to different regions and tribes with dates and celebrations marked by differing positions of the sun, moon and stars. Names of months and holidays, as well as the corresponding dates in the Gregorian Calendar, vary widely from one calendar to the next. Use our dates as a baseline. Find out which of the dozens of Hindu calendars is used in the region you live or plan to visit if you are looking to attend or witness a specific observance. ', 'Hindu Religious Event. See The Hindu Temple Society of North America for more information', 'New York Ganesh Temple', ' 45-57 Bowne Street', ' Flushing', 'NY', 'US', '11355', '(718) 460.8484  ', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', 'Media Relations', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/