(91, 'US Open Golf Championship (US-NC): June 13-16', 'United States', '6', '13', '2024', '2024-06-13', '6', '16', '2024', '2024-06-16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '45', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.usga.org', NULL, NULL, 'About the US Open Golf Championship', NULL, 'The US Open Golf Championship is sponsored by the United States Golf Association, and is often held on the third Sunday of June. The event is one of the four major golf tournaments in the world. ', 'United States Golf Association', '77 Liberty Corner Rd', NULL, 'Far Hills', 'NJ', 'US', '7931', '(908) 234.2300', 'http://www.usga.org/contact-us.html', 'General Information', 'http://www.usga.org/contact-us.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, 'Pinehurst Resort, Pinehurst NC', NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-17 16:50:23', '2021-01-17 16:50:23'),
(92, 'Pastoral Care Week: October 20-26', 'Worldwide', '10', '20', '2024', '2024-10-20', '10', '26', '2024', '2024-10-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '38', '35', '10', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.pastoralcareweek.org/pastandfuturethemes.html', NULL, NULL, 'About National Pastoral Care Week', NULL, 'Organizations and institutions throughout the world will recognize the spiritual needs of those we serve and the spiritual care given through professional chaplaincy and pastoral counseling within our communities. Chaplains, pastoral care counselors, educators and care providers will share in this year’s theme, “Spiritual Resilience.”\n \nRegardless of spiritual, religious or cultural background, Pastoral Care Week celebrates those who provide spiritual support to others.  It is supported by the Coalition On Ministry In Specialized Settings Network:  The Network on Ministries in Specialized Settings, whose members provide care in specialized settings such as hospitals, prisons, businesses, industries, long-term care facilities, pastoral counseling centers, hospices, military settings, nursing homes, corporations, congregations of sisters, priests and brothers, schools and universities throughout the world. \n \nThis year’s theme, “Spiritual Resilience,” acknowledges the role of Chaplains and Pastoral Counselors to support the spiritual resilience or growth of it in those we serve.  Spiritual Resilience represents one’s ability to navigate through, or recover from, life’s most challenging moments.  Spiritual Resilience finds its roots in one’s sense of spirituality and related practices, religion or beliefs, values, and outlook.  It also represents the individual’s ability to gain, maintain or revise a sense of purpose and meaning, relationships, connections to the sacred, nature, and understanding of themselves and the world around them.  These traumatic life events and losses invite the professional who can nurture spiritual resiliency.  Pastoral/Spiritual Care week provides a unique opportunity to both have a conversation to address suffering related to loss and trauma and to seek opportunities for strengthening spiritual resilience amid them. \n \nMany institutions will celebrate Pastoral Care Week by honoring the work and gifts of pastoral/spiritual care givers locally and internationally, as well as the spiritual needs of those who serve.  Among the variety of celebrations will be hand-blessing ceremonies for health workers; open houses; poetry jams by clients; lecture series and luncheons.', 'COMISS Network', 'Pastoral Care Week', '16806 Windsor Park Drive', 'Lutz', 'FL', 'US', '33549', '(800) 318.3849', 'kballard@chmca.org ', 'General Information', 'http://www.pastoralcareweek.org/contactus.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-17 16:50:23', '2021-01-17 16:50:23');
