(95, 'Patient Protection & Affordable Care Act Signed into Law (2010): March 23', 'United States', '3', '23', '2025', '2025-03-23', '3', '23', '2025', '2025-03-23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '36', '20', '25', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient_Protection_and_Affordable_Care_Act', NULL, NULL, 'About the  Patient Protection & Affordable Care Act Becoming Law', NULL, 'Fifteen Year Anniversary. March 23, 2010 was the day when the Patient Protection & Affordable Care Act (PPACA) was signed into Law in the U.S. Commonly known as the Affordable Care Act (ACA) or just Obamacare its institution split the nation in two. \n\nTogether with the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act, this act was the biggest and most significant regulatory overhaul of the U.S. healthcare system since 1965, when Medicare and Medicaid were added.', 'US Government: U.S. General Services Administration', 'Office of Citizen Services and Innovative Technologies', '1800 F Street, NW', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20405', '(800) 333.4636', 'http://answers.usa.gov/system/templates/selfservice/USAGov/#!portal/1012/email_us', 'Citizen Services', 'http://www.usa.gov/Contact-Us.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-17 16:50:23', '2021-01-17 16:50:23'),
