(115, 'Princess Diana Dies  (UK)(1997): August 31', 'United Kingdom', '8', '31', '2027', '2027-08-31', '8', '31', '2027', '2027-08-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '49', '36', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.biography.com/people/princess-diana-9273782', NULL, NULL, 'About the Anniversary of Princess Diana\'s Death', NULL, 'Thirtieth Anniversary. It was on August 31, 1997 when Diana, Princess of Wales died in a car crash in Pont de l’Alma, a road tunnel in Paris. \n\nPassengers in the car included friend Dodi Fayed and her bodyguard Trevor Rees-Jones, the only survivor. Their driver Henri Paul, also perished at the scene. \n\nWhile the accident was blamed on the chasing paparazzi, further investigation concluded that it was caused by loss of control of the car by the driver who was also under the influence of alcohol. She was pronounced dead at 4 in the morning.\n\nPrincess Diana was referred to as the ‘People’s Princess’.  She lent her time to several philanthropic activities and consistently worked to further the interests of mankind.  She is survived by her two sons, The Duke of Cambridge and Prince Henry. ', 'Historical Anniversary.  See The Royal Foundation for topical info. ', 'The Royal Foundation Of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry', 'Kensington Palace, Palace Green', 'London', ' ', 'UK', 'W8 4PU', ' ', 'info@royalfoundation.com', 'General Information', 'http://www.royalfoundation.com/contact-us/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-17 16:50:23', '2021-01-17 16:50:23'),
(116, 'Sandy Super Storm (2012): October 29', 'United States', '10', '29', '2027', '2027-10-29', '10', '29', '2027', '2027-10-29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '15', '18', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052970204840504578084550304936518.html', NULL, NULL, 'About the Anniversary of Sandy Super Storm', NULL, 'This is the fifteenth anniversary of Sandy Super Storm in 2012. It was on this day when Sandy hit the East Coast and left 730,000 people with no power, costing about $75 billion (surpassed only by Hurricane Katrina) and killing at least 233 people in a total of eight counties. ', 'Historical Anniversary. No Sponsor. ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-17 16:50:23', '2021-01-17 16:50:23'),
