(119, 'Utoeya (NO) Massacre (2011): July 22', 'Norway', '7', '22', '2026', '2026-07-22', '7', '22', '2026', '2026-07-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '36', '16', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/23/us-norway-blast-idUSTRE76L2VI20110723', NULL, NULL, 'About the Utoeya Massacre in Norway', NULL, '15th Anniversary. It was on July 22, 2011 that the Utoeya Massacre occurred.  Carried out by Anders Behring Breivik, the sequential attacks were aimed against the government, the civilians and the Worker’ Youth League (AUF), which claimed 77 lives. \n\nThere were two attacks, the first of which was a car bomb that exploded in the executive department area in Oslo that killed 8 lives and injured hundreds of people. Placed in the back part of the van, the bomb was made of fertilizer and fuel oil. The van was placed near the office of Prime Minister Jens Stoltenberg. \n\nThe second attack occurred after two hours the first bomb detonated. It was at a summer camp in the island of Utoeya where Breivik, who was wearing a police uniform and showing falsified identification openly fired killing 68 right then and there and injuring 110 people. The 69th victim died in a hospital due to the seriousness of injuries. On August 24, 2012, Breivik was sentenced to 21 years of preventive detention.\n', 'Historical Event. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-20 03:44:52', '2021-01-20 03:44:52'),
