(126, 'Princess Diana Dies  (UK)(1997): August 31', 'United Kingdom', '8', '31', '2027', '2027-08-31', '8', '31', '2027', '2027-08-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '49', '36', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.biography.com/people/princess-diana-9273782', NULL, NULL, 'About the Anniversary of Princess Diana\'s Death', NULL, 'Thirtieth Anniversary. It was on August 31, 1997 when Diana, Princess of Wales died in a car crash in Pont de l’Alma, a road tunnel in Paris. \n\nPassengers in the car included friend Dodi Fayed and her bodyguard Trevor Rees-Jones, the only survivor. Their driver Henri Paul, also perished at the scene. \n\nWhile the accident was blamed on the chasing paparazzi, further investigation concluded that it was caused by loss of control of the car by the driver who was also under the influence of alcohol. She was pronounced dead at 4 in the morning.\n\nPrincess Diana was referred to as the ‘People’s Princess’.  She lent her time to several philanthropic activities and consistently worked to further the interests of mankind.  She is survived by her two sons, The Duke of Cambridge and Prince Henry. ', 'Historical Anniversary.  See The Royal Foundation for topical info. ', 'The Royal Foundation Of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge and Prince Harry', 'Kensington Palace, Palace Green', 'London', ' ', 'UK', 'W8 4PU', ' ', 'info@royalfoundation.com', 'General Information', 'http://www.royalfoundation.com/contact-us/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-20 03:44:52', '2021-01-20 03:44:52'),
