(130, 'Utoeya (NO) Massacre (2011): July 22', 'Norway', '7', '22', '2026', '2026-07-22', '7', '22', '2026', '2026-07-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '36', '16', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/23/us-norway-blast-idUSTRE76L2VI20110723', NULL, NULL, 'About the Utoeya Massacre in Norway', NULL, '15th Anniversary. It was on July 22, 2011 that the Utoeya Massacre occurred.  Carried out by Anders Behring Breivik, the sequential attacks were aimed against the government, the civilians and the Worker’ Youth League (AUF), which claimed 77 lives. \n\nThere were two attacks, the first of which was a car bomb that exploded in the executive department area in Oslo that killed 8 lives and injured hundreds of people. Placed in the back part of the van, the bomb was made of fertilizer and fuel oil. The van was placed near the office of Prime Minister Jens Stoltenberg. \n\nThe second attack occurred after two hours the first bomb detonated. It was at a summer camp in the island of Utoeya where Breivik, who was wearing a police uniform and showing falsified identification openly fired killing 68 right then and there and injuring 110 people. The 69th victim died in a hospital due to the seriousness of injuries. On August 24, 2012, Breivik was sentenced to 21 years of preventive detention.\n', 'Historical Event. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-20 03:47:02', '2021-01-20 03:47:02'),
(131, 'Palestine Petitions for Statehood (2011): September 24', 'Israel & Palestine Territories', '9', '24', '2026', '2026-09-24', '9', '24', '2026', '2026-09-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '59', '36', '62', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Foreign-Policy/2011/0926/How-US-could-avoid-vetoing-Palestinian-statehood', NULL, NULL, 'About the Historical Anniversary of Palestine Petitioning for Statehood', NULL, 'Fifteenth Anniversary. Today marks the anniversary of Palestine’s 2011 petition for statehood. \n\nParts of Palestine since 1948 and the whole of Palestine since 1967 have been occupied by the nation state of Israel. The diplomatic campaign \"Palestine 194\" of 2011 helped Palestine reach the status of non-member observer state by the UN. This status was later formally backed by the Arab League and officially confirmed by the Palestine Liberation Organization.', 'Historical Anniversary. See UN for details.', 'UN Department of Public Information', ' ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10017', '(212) 963.7160', 'malu@un.org', 'Media Liaison', 'http://www.un.org/en/media/accreditation/contact.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-20 03:47:02', '2021-01-20 03:47:02'),
(132, 'Gadhafi Assassination (2011): October 20', 'Libya', '10', '20', '2026', '2026-10-20', '10', '20', '2026', '2026-10-20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '29', '36', '64', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/oct/23/gaddafi-last-words-begged-mercy', NULL, NULL, 'About the Gadhafi Assassination in 2011', NULL, 'Today marks the 15th anniversary of the assassination of Libya’s Muammar Gaddafi. \n\nThe NATO campaign, known as \"Operation Unified Protector\", aimed to remove the head of a country, that was in direct violation of international law as established by the Geneva Conventions after the Nuremberg trials at the end of World War II.', 'Historic Anniversary. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-20 03:47:02', '2021-01-20 03:47:02'),
(133, 'Trayvon Martin Murder (2012): February 26', 'United States', '2', '26', '2027', '2027-02-26', '2', '26', '2027', '2027-02-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '36', '25', '59', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.democracynow.org/2012/3/20/a_modern_day_lynching_outrage_grows', '6753_Trayvon_Martin_MurderF.jpg', '6753_Trayvon_Martin_MurderE.jpg', 'About the Trayvon Martin Anniversary of his murder', NULL, 'This is the 15th Anniversary of the shooting of Trayvon Benjamin Martin (February 5, 1995 – February 26, 2012). \n\nTrayvon was the son of Sybrina Fulton and Tracy Martin, was shot dead by George Zimmerman on February 26, 2012, in a residential neighborhood in Florida. The young man was walking down the street, drinking and ice tea and speaking to his girlfriend on the phone when Zimmerman confronted him and shot him. He was a junior at Dr. Michael M. Krop High School and just 17 years of age. He dreamed of attending college and becoming an aviation mechanic or pilot. On the day Martin was fatally shot, he and his father were visiting his father’s fiancée and her son at her townhome in Sanford, Florida.\n\nZimmerman was acquitted of murder under the state of Florida’s “Stand your Ground” laws which allow a citizen to shoot another citizen if they feel threatened. The death of Trayvon reignited the race debate as Trayvon was black and Zimmerman white. \n\nIn memory of their son’s death, the family set up the Trayvon Martin Foundation with a purpose is to create awareness of how violent crime impacts the families of the victims and to provide support and advocacy for those families in response to the murder of Trayvon Martin. Today is the day people the world over remember the young man and the senseless way in which he died.', 'Historical Anniversary. See The Trayvon Martin Foundation for details', 'The Trayvon Martin Foundation', '200 S Biscayne Boulevard Ste. 505', 'Miami', 'FL', 'US', '33131', '(305) 600.8810', 'http://trayvonmartinfoundation.org/contact-us/', 'Media Relations', 'http://trayvonmartinfoundation.org/contact-us/', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/PVOqbkBD1vw?feature=player_embedded\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/DZXY7mAEzJg\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/DZXY7mAEzJg\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/mBRDvSd0AJc\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Approved', '2021-01-20 03:47:02', '2021-01-20 03:47:02'),
