(192, 'AVN Awards (US-NV): January 25', 'United States', '1', '25', '2020', '2020-01-25', '1', '25', '2020', '2020-01-25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '14', '40', '27', '67', '51', '52', 'Daily', 'Changes', ' ', 'https://avn.com/awards', NULL, NULL, 'About the AVN Awards in Las Vegas', NULL, 'The AVN Awards are the annual adult entertainment awards. It recognizes and celebrates business excellence and outstanding performance by professionals, companies and actors within the adult entertainment industry.\n\nPLEASE NOTE:\n\nAll televised and venue specific events (sporting, concerts, trade shows, etc.) should be treated as estimated, even if the dates are set. Several factors can cause an event to change dates at the last minute including weather, strikes, natural disasters, political upheaval, conflicting programming and current events. Because of this, always verify the event with the promotor prior to committing resources. In many cases we must estimate the dates based upon previous years\' schedules, as the final dates are not set until a few months or weeks prior to the event. If the date is known to be estimated, you will see an (est) following the date in the title. ', 'AVN Media Network, Inc.', '9400 Penfield Avenue ', NULL, 'Chatsworth', 'CA', 'US', '91311', '(818) 718.5788', 'http://avn.com/contact-us', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.avnmedianetwork.com/contacts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Hard Rock Hotel & Casino, Las Vegas, Nevada, US', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(193, 'Babinden (RU/BG): January 23', 'Bulgaria, Russia', '1', '23', '2020', '2020-01-23', '1', '23', '2020', '2020-01-23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '50', '9', '10', '66', '65', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://intrepidexposures.com/travel-stories/winter-festivals-bulgaria-babinden/', NULL, NULL, 'About Babinden', NULL, 'Babinden is a Bulgarian traditional observance celebrated in Russia and known as the Day of the Midwives. On this day, women and children under three rise at dawn and head to the local well where they draw water and infuse it with basil or geranium. This is drunk before heading off to the midwife\'s house. She is bathed by the mothers and presented with a bouquet of geraniums tied in red and white ribbon (symbolizing a healthy child with rosy cheeks). The ribbons are then removed and a silver coin added. These coins and ribbon are then tied to the child born of the midwife, who also receives new socks and shirts. The custom in Bulgaria is that a child is blessed each of its first three years on this day by the midwife to promote a long healthy life. Another pitcher of water is drawn, infused with basil or geraniums and taken to the local church to be blessed.  This water is then used by the mother, a little bit each day, to bathe for the next forty. \n\nAt noon, the party moves to the midwife\'s house again where a feast is prepared by the mother and her female relatives for lunch. This female only feast is rich with banter, jokes and singing. Upon its conclusion, the men are allowed to join in the rest of the day\'s festivities, usually dressed as oxen and pulling a cart through town holding the midwife. If they run across any women, the men must pay a ransom to pass.', 'Bulgarian and Russian Tradition. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(194, 'Baby Making Day (UK) Ntl.: January 2', 'United Kingdom', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '40', '9', '49', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/national-baby-making-day-conceive_uk_5a4b4ad8e4b025f99e1d305c', NULL, NULL, 'About National Baby Making Day in the UK', NULL, 'What is the most popular birthday in the United Kingdom? \n\nSeptember 26.\n\nWhat does that mean?\n\nMore Brits make babies 38-weeks earlier on January 2 (between 10PM and 11:00PM GMT, with 10:36PM being the most amorous minute of the year) than at any other time of the year. So warm up the sheets, get out the lingerie and oils and get ready to do your patriot duty United Kingdom. Celebrate Baby Making Day the best way you can...canoodling for the future!', 'Statistical Event. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(195, 'Backwards Day: January 31', 'Worldwide', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '44', '13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://blog.hope-education.co.uk/early-years/classroom-ideas-celebrate-national-backwards-day/', NULL, NULL, 'About Backwards Day', NULL, 'Backwards Day is an organic celebration with no sponsor, celebrated worldwide. The basic concept of the day? Do everything in reverse.  Eat dessert first. Call people by their last name. Read a book back to front. Back into your parking space. See how many palindromes you can identify, (words spelled the same forward and back). You get the idea! \n\nHistorically there is something called “Backwards Day,” but there is no specific reason for designating January 31 to observe it. \n\nThe original Backwards Day occurred in the  Julian Calendar (45BC-1582), the predecessor of the modern Gregorian calendar. Day one of the Gregorian calendar is October 15, 1582, (though it would be the mid 1700s before it became the standard in Europe and the rest of the world).  \n\nBecause the Sun’s rotation around the earth is just shy of 365 days, the way the Roman’s dealt with this was to shift the calendar backwards one day every 128 years. With the rise of Christianity, this became a problem. Easter is determined by the vernal equinox and over the course of centuries, the Julian calendar caused the vernal equinox to move backwards by 10 days. \n\nThe Gregorian calendar, with its leap year every four years, solved this problem. The Gregorian calendar also assured that the vernal equinox would always fall at the same time every year.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See U.S. Department of Commerce, (NIST) for topical info.', 'National Institute for Standards and Technology (NIST), Time and Frequency Division', '325 Broadway, M/S 847', 'Boulder', 'CO', 'US', '80305-3328', '(303) 497.3295', 'michael.douma@idea.org.', 'Michael Douma, Curator Calendars through the Ages', 'http://www.nist.gov/pml/div688/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(196, 'Bagel Day, Ntl.: January 15', 'United States', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://thomasbreads.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Bagel Day', NULL, 'First held in 2014, National Bagel Day celebrates the doughnut shaped circular bread that has become a breakfast and lunch favorite in America. The bagel originated in Krakow Poland in 1610.', 'Bimbo Bakeries USA', 'PO Box 96', NULL, 'Horsham', 'PA', 'US', '19044', '(800) 984.0989', 'https://www.bimbobakeriesusa.com/contact-us', 'General Information', 'https://www.bimbobakeriesusa.com/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(197, 'Bald Eagle Appreciation Days (US-IA): January 18-19', 'United States', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '15', '13', '51', '52', ' ', 'Daily', 'Changes', '3rd Weekend Jan', 'http://www.keokuk.net/tourism/bald.htm', 'Bald_Eagle_DaysF.jpg', 'Bald_Eagle_DaysE.jpg', 'About National Bald Eagle Appreciation Days', NULL, 'During the late fall and winter months bald eagles flock to Iowa where it is much warmer than their summer home of Alaska and Canada. In Alaska and Canada the rivers freeze over so over 1,400 bald eagles follow the river south and spend the coldest months of the year along the Mississippi river between St. Paul and St. Louis. The highest percentage live in the area of Keokuk. \n\nEach year U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Non Game Wildlife programs within the Iowa Department of Natural Resources and Illinois Department of Conservation, Lee County Conservation Board, Keosippi Mall and The Keokuk Area Convention and Tourism Bureau host Bald Eagle Appreciation Days the 3rd weekend of January. Thousands of people flock to Keokuk to view first hand the national symbol of the United States of America in its natural surroundings. \n\nBald Eagle Appreciation Days feature many free indoor and outdoor programs including:\n\n • Hourly seminars featuring live Bald Eagles\n • Lectures\n • Exhibits\n • Films\n • Special events\n • Manned observation areas along the Mississippi Riverfront\n • Spotting scopes available\n • Conservation officials and biologists on hand for questions\n\nTips for finding and viewing eagles:\n\nThe best time to view eagles is in the early morning. This is their prime feeding time when they can be seen soaring and diving for fish, and the colder, the better. When eagles are not feeding they can be seen most often sitting in large, mature trees closer to the river. They are also commonly seen on river ice near openings. Strong binoculars or a spotting scope are usually necessary for eagle viewing unless you are lucky. They are only a few locations where they are not needed.', 'U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Non Game Wildlife programs ', 'Keokuk Area Convention and Tourism Bureau ', '401 Main Street', 'Keokuk', 'IA', 'US', '52632', '(319) 524.5599', NULL, 'Media Relations', 'http://www.keokuk.net', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Keosippi Mall 300 Main St; Keokuk, Iowa 52632', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(198, 'Bath Safety Month, Ntl.: January ', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '42', '37', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.prweb.com/releases/2016/01/prweb13151111.htm ', NULL, NULL, 'About National Bath Safety Month', NULL, 'A soothing warm shower is one of the best parts of the day, but it can also be dangerous if homeowners aren’t careful. Slippery floors in and around the shower stall can cause falls and injuries. In fact, two-thirds of all bathroom injuries treated at emergency departments occurred in the tub or shower, according to a 2008 study by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. \n\nNational Bath Safety Month in January is embraced by Moen. The company provides bath safety tips and statistics to educate consumers on the importance of bath safety and how they can make easy, impactful updates to their homes … without sacrificing style.\n\n“We’ve heard so many stories from consumers sharing ways bath safety has made a difference in their lives,” said Chris Nealon, wholesale product manager, Moen.\n\n“How a shower seat helped a pregnant mom avoid slipping while shaving. An athlete with a broken leg who could shower without assistance … thanks to a grab bar. How a grab bar with shelf helped a grandparent feel secure while bathing – and provided a spot to store bath toys for visiting grandkids. \n\nIt’s these stories and more that inspired the \'My Bath Safety Story\' promotion. \n\nBy creating an avenue for homeowners to share their stories, we hope we’ll inspire others to incorporate bath safety products into their bathrooms, no matter their age or level of physical fitness. Bath safety really is important for anyone at any age.\"', 'Fortune Brands Home & Security, Inc. ', '520 Lake Cook Road', 'Suite 300', 'Deerfield', 'IL', 'US', '60015', '(216) 696.0229 ', 'jallanson@fallscommunications.com', 'Jennifer Allanson ', 'http://www.prweb.com/releases/2016/01/prweb13151111.htm', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JhxKBaPcsAk\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
