(200, 'Be on Purpose Month: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '44', '26', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://worksmartlivesmart.com/national-be-on-purpose-month-january/', NULL, NULL, 'About Be on Purpose Month', NULL, 'Be on Purpose Month is an unofficial observance without a sponsor. The objective of this month is to encourage people to make an effort with their New Years Resolution: Be purposeful and make it count. ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See On Purpose Partners for ideas', 'On Purpose Partners ', 'PO Box 1568', 'Winter Park', 'FL', 'US', '32790', '(407) 657.6000', 'http://on-purpose.com/contact/', 'Media Relations', 'http://on-purpose.com/contact/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(201, 'Bean Day (1884): January 6', 'United States', '1', '6', '2020', '2020-01-06', '1', '6', '2020', '2020-01-06', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '43', '19', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/01/06/national-bean-day-why-its_n_805328.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Bean Day', NULL, 'Today marks the anniversary of the death of Austrian scientist Gregor Mendel in 1884. Mendel is the founder of the modern field of Genetics and performed his work through the study of beans and legumes. He is the person who identified and described what we now call dominant and recessive genes. \n\nBecause he died in the late 19th Century, Mendel never realized how important his discoveries and work was. He laid the foundation for 20th Century advances in therapies and medicines, agriculture and science. ', 'Historical Event.  See the Mendel Museum of Genetics for Background', 'MENDEL MUSEUM, Masaryk University', 'Mendlovo nám. 1a', 'Brno', ' ', 'CZ', '603 00', '(+42)(0) 549.496.669', 'info@mendelmuseum.muni.cz', 'Media Relations', 'http://mendelmuseum.muni.cz/en/information-and-contacts/general-info', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'WhatCanYouDoWith_Beans.pdf', NULL, NULL, 'How to Use Canned Beans in Your Diet', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(202, 'Beer Can Appreciation Day (1935): January 24', 'Worldwide', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '1', '46', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.bcca.com/beer-can-history/ ', NULL, NULL, 'About National Beer Can Appreciation Day', NULL, 'It was on January 24, 1935 that the beer can we know today, a radical change from glass bottles, went on sale. Beer Can Appreciation Day marks this anniversary. \n\nThe packaging concept was created by Krueger\'s Finest Beer.', 'Historical Event.  See Brewery Collectibles Club of America for History', 'Brewery Collectibles Club of America', '747 Merus Court', 'Fenton', 'MO', 'US', '63026-2092', '(636) 343.6486', 'bcca@bcca.com', 'General Information', 'http://www.bcca.com/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(203, 'Bell, Let\'s Talk Day (CA): January 30', 'Canada', '1', '30', '2020', '2020-01-30', '1', '30', '2020', '2020-01-30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '26', '11', '7', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://letstalk.bell.ca', NULL, NULL, 'About Canada\'s Bell Let\'s Talk Day', NULL, 'Focused on mental illness, Bell Let\'s Talk was created in 2010 to raise awareness about the millions of Canadians struggling with mental illness and remove the stigma of discussing it. This is also a national fundraising event for Bell Canada and its work in mental health. ', 'Bell Canada', '1 Carrefour Alexander-Graham-Bell', 'Building A, 4th Floor', 'Verdun', 'QC', 'CA', 'H3E 3B3', '(888) 932.6666', 'bcecomms@bce.ca', 'General  Information', 'http://www.bce.ca/contact-us/general-information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(204, 'Belly Laugh Day, Global.: January 24', 'Worldwide', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.bellylaughday.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Belly Laugh Day', NULL, 'On 1/24 each year at 1:24pm local time, people throw their arms up in the air and laugh as loud as they can in celebration of Global Belly Laugh Day.  \n\nUltimately, the goal of this day is to share the gift of laughter with those around. \n\nFollow the Belly Laugh Bounce around the world clock here: \nhttp://www.bellylaughday.com/124laughbounce.html\n\nGlobal Belly Laugh Day was created in 2005 and first celebrated in 2006.', 'Global Belly Laugh Day', ' ', ' ', 'Portland', 'OR', 'US', ' ', ' ', 'jan24@bellylaughday.com', 'Elaine Helle', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/elaine-helle-4930002a ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(205, 'Big Wig Day, Ntl.: January 31', 'United States', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '8', '11', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Last Friday January', 'https://nationalbigwigday.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Big Wig Day', NULL, 'The term \'Big Wig\' originated in 1730s Europe. The wealthier you were, the larger the wig you wore. Large or big wigs were then an outward sign of a wealthy important person. In centuries later, the term would come to mean the boss or person in authority.\n\nNational Big Wig Day has less august ambitions. It started as silliness in 2016 and as a way to brighten up a lackluster mid-winter day. It turned into a fundraiser for people struggling with cancer and enduring chemotherapy. Hair loss is one of the symptoms of this. \n\nThe best way to celebrate, sport your favorite wig today and go to the website for the event and choose a charity to donate to including: \n\nAmerican Cancer Society\n\nLook Good Feel Better\n\nDesert Cancer Foundation of Coachella Valley\n\nHospitality House of Boone, North Carolina\n\nUnited Way\n\nEach year sees more charities join. Check the site for the most updated list. ', 'Sharkey Films, LLC', '1833 South Araby Drive ', NULL, 'Palm Springs', 'CA', 'US', '92264', '(949) 294.5695', 'info@nationalbigwigday.com', 'Patty Sharkey', 'https://www.facebook.com/pg/bigwigday/about', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(206, 'Biodiversity, UN Decade on: 2011-2020', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2011', '2011-01-01', '12', '31', '2020', '2020-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '15', '20', '59', '43', NULL, 'Decade', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.cbd.int/2011-2020/', NULL, NULL, 'About the UN Decade on Biodiversity', NULL, 'Signed at the Earth Summit in Rio de Janeiro in 1992 and put in force in December 1993, the Convention on Biological Diversity is an international treaty for the conservation of biodiversity. Biodiversity involves the sustainable use of the components of our natural world and the equitable sharing of the benefits derived from the use of genetic resources. \n\nWith 196 Parties so far, the Convention has near universal participation among countries. The Convention seeks to address all threats to biodiversity and ecosystem services, including threats from climate change, through scientific assessments, the development of tools, incentives and processes, the transfer of technologies and good practices and the full and active involvement of relevant stakeholders including indigenous and local communities, youth, NGOs, women and the business community. \n\nThe purpose of declaring a decade for a specific event is to allow time to develop and deploy initiatives that move the entire planet closer to the goal. The UN Decade on Biodiversity encompasses the years 2011-2020', 'United Nations', 'Department of Public Information', ' ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10017', '(212) 963.7160', 'malu@un.org', 'Media Liaison', 'http://www.un.org/en/media/accreditation/contact.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(207, 'Bird Day, Ntl.: January 5', 'United States', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '15', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.nationalbirdday.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Bird Day', NULL, 'Each year for three weeks during the Christmas season the wild bird population (over 9,600 species) of the world is counted.  It is estimated today that twelve percent of these species face extinction. Threats to bird populations include illegal pet trade, disease, pollution, loss of habitat, disease and solar panels and other technological advances.  The Christmas Count, which began in the early 2000s, is the longest running citizen science survey in the world. \n\nNational Bird Day occurs on January 5 each year to mark the conclusion of the Christmas count and bring the focus away from wild birds to those kept in captivity within the United States, most of which are pets and native to other countries. The ultimate goal of National Bird Day is to increase the survival rate and well-being of the world\'s birds through public education and support for conservation.\n\nThis event first ran in 2002. ', 'Born Free USA ', 'P.O. Box 32160', ' ', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20007', '(202) 450.3168', 'press@bornfreeusa.org ', 'Media Relations ', 'http://www.bornfreeusa.org/d6_contact.php', NULL, NULL, NULL, '9023_Bird_Lifecycle_Wheel.pdf', '9023_Bird_Anatomy_Puzzle.pdf', '9023_Go_On_birdwalk.pdf', 'Lifecycle of birds in PDF', 'Teacher Tools: Anatomy of Birds Puzzle', 'Teacher Tools: How to create a bird watching walk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(208, 'Birth Defects Prevention Month, Ntl.: January ', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '9', '50', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'www.nbdpn.org', NULL, NULL, 'About National Birth Defects Prevention Month', NULL, 'National Birth Defects Prevention Network sponsors National Birth Defects Prevention Month each year.  \n\nSee the consortium’s website for details on this year’s focus and to download materials and study aids.', 'National Birth Defects Prevention Network', '1321 Upland Drive', 'Suite 1561', 'Houston', 'TX', 'US', '77043', NULL, 'nbdpn@nbdpn.org ', 'General Information', 'http://www.nbdpn.org/contact_us.php', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(209, 'Bittersweet Chocolate Day: January 10', 'United States', '1', '10', '2020', '2020-01-10', '1', '10', '2020', '2020-01-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.northjersey.com/story/life/columnists/bill-ervolino/2018/01/10/need-something-celebrate-its-bittersweet-chocolate-day/1020204001/', NULL, NULL, 'About Bittersweet Chocolate Day', NULL, 'Dark chocolate in Europe, or bittersweet baker’s chocolate in the Americas, is a minimum of 35% pure cocoa with little or no sweetener added.  Of all the chocolates in the world, dark chocolate is the most versatile and can be used in baking, eaten with wine and/or cheese. ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Fine Chocolate Industry Association for topical info./details', 'Fine Chocolate Industry Association', '4701 SW Admiral Way #324', 'Seattle', 'WA', 'US', '98116', '(206) 577.9983', 'maryjo@FineChocolateIndustry.org', 'Mary Jo Stojak, Executive Director', 'http://www.finechocolateindustry.org/ballyhoo', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(210, 'Black Hills Stock Show & Rodeo (US-SD): January 24-February 2', 'United States', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '2', '2', '2020', '2020-02-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '45', '51', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://www.blackhillsstockshow.com', NULL, NULL, 'About the Black Hills Stock Show & Rodeo', NULL, 'Riding competitions, livestock and entertainment, the annual Black Hills Stock Show and Rodeo is an annual bright spot in the otherwise harsh and cold Dakota winters.\n\nThe event was created in 1958 as a means to bring together the rural and urban communities of Rapid City, South Dakota. It\'s grown in popularity and importance ever since. ', 'Central States Fair, Inc', '800 San Francisco St', NULL, 'Rapid City', 'SD', 'US', '57701', '(605) 355.3861', 'info@blackhillsstockshow.com', 'General Information', 'https://www.blackhillsstockshow.com/contact.aspx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rapid City, South Dakota, US', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(211, 'Black Nazarene Fiesta (PH): January 1-9', 'Philippines', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '10', '69', '63', NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.quiapochurch.com', NULL, NULL, 'About Black Nazarene Fiesta in Manila', NULL, 'Black Nazarene Fiesta is observed annually in Manila, Philippines. It culminates in a parade originating from the Quiapo Church featuring a life-size statue of the district’s patron saint, Black Nazarene. Fireworks, food, music and an outpouring of culture are all part of this multi-day celebration. ', 'LBN Foundation', '910 Plaza Miranda', NULL, 'Manila', NULL, 'PH', NULL, '(+63)(02) 522.0393', 'lbnfoundation@yahoo.com.ph', 'General Information', 'http://www.quiapochurch.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Quiapo Church, Manila, Philippines', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(212, 'Blonde Brownie Day, Ntl.: January 22', 'United States', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://allrecipes.com/recipe/blonde-brownies-i', NULL, NULL, 'About National Blonde Brownie Day', NULL, 'National Blonde Brownie Day recognizes the blonde brownie, which is actually the first brownie ever included in a cookbook, The Boston Cooking-School Cookbook by Fanny Merrit Farmer in 1896. \n\nThis book changed the way American families cook. It was written in a teaching format rather than simply recipes. It is possible that the day chosen for Blond Brownie Day coincides with the date of release for the book. We are unable to confirm that though. \n\nIt wouldn’t be until 1898 that the words chocolate and brownie would finally appear together in an advertisement in the Kansas City Journal, and 1899 before a chocolate brownie recipe would be published.\n \nBlonde brownies contain zero chocolate and are basically cookies baked in a pan and cut into rectangles.  \n\nToday we often do this with chocolate chip cookie dough in an effort to shorten the amount of time it takes to cook the cookies one sheet at a time. Technically, these pan chocolate chip cookies would be brownies. \nWhat differentiates a brownie from cookies and cake is the density of the finished product.  \n\nCookies tend to be flat and dense. \nCake is high and light. \nBrownies are high and dense. ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group for History', 'Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group ', '1745 Broadway ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10019', ' ', 'knopfpublicity@randomhouse.com ', 'Publicity Department', 'http://knopfdoubleday.com/contact-us/ ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(213, 'Blood Donor Month, Ntl.: January ', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.redcross.org/news/event/January-is-National-Blood-Donor-Month', NULL, NULL, 'About National Blood Donor Month', NULL, 'Each year the American Red Cross sponsors National Blood Donor Month in an effort to restock the nation’s supply of blood.\n\nYou don\'t need a special reason to give blood. You just need your own reason.\n\nSome of us give blood because we were asked by a friend. Some know that a family member or a friend might need blood some day. Some believe it is the right thing to do.\n\nWhatever your reason, the need is constant and your donation is important for maintaining a healthy and reliable blood supply. You\'ll feel good knowing you\'ve helped change a life!', 'American Red Cross', '2025 E Street, NW', NULL, 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20006', '(202) 303.5551', 'http://www.redcross.org/contact-us/general-inquiry', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.redcross.org/contact-us/general-inquiry', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(214, 'Bloody Mary Day: January 1', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.twoop.com/food_drink/archives/2005/10/bloody_mary_cocktail.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Bloody Mary Day', NULL, 'The 18th Amendment and the Russian Revolution are responsible for the favorite hangover cocktail cure known as the Bloody Mary. \n\nThe 18th Amendment forced Americans who enjoyed libations overseas to find relief from prohibition. Meanwhile, on the other side of the world a revolution was in full swing. People escaping Russia brought with them their favorite distilled spirit. Both groups of refugees converged in Paris.  \n\nDuring this time Harry Mac Elhone built an authentic New York bar in Paris, complete with the original bar shipped in from the States. The French found this novelty delightful. Americans sought it out as a taste of home and the Russians, well, they just wanted to have a good time.  \n\nMac Elhone found vodka to be rather tasteless and boring. His bartender Ferdinand “Pet” Petiot spent months fooling around with the liquor, attempting to make something novel. Then one day he combined it with tomato juice cocktail and spices. Bam! The Bloody Mary was born…except it was called Bucket of Blood. Then, the Red Snapper. \n\nTo get to the name Bloody Mary would require the end of Prohibition and a trip back to New York, specifically at the King Cole Bar in the St. Regis Hotel.  Petiot was lured back by the Astors.\n\nThere are several stories as to why the Red Snapper morphed into Bloody Mary. Some say it pays homage to Mary Tudor I of England, Queen Elizabeth I’s half sister who was famous for killing Protestants. Or possibly after actor George Jessel friend, Mary Geraghty. Or simply because it was easier to remember than Red Snapper and more appealing than bucket of blood. However, the drink received its name, by 1946 the drink was thus called in print. \n\nJanuary 1 is dubbed Bloody Mary Day simply because on New Years Eve, people tend to drink too much and thus need this hangover cure, first thing in the morning.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See The King Cole Bar', 'St. Regis Hotel', '2 E 55th St ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10022', '(212) 339.6857', 'stregisny.res@stregis.com', 'King Cole Bar', 'http://www.starwoodhotels.com/stregis/property/overview/contact.html?propertyID=81 ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(215, 'Blueberry Pancake Day: January 28', 'United States', '1', '28', '2020', '2020-01-28', '1', '28', '2020', '2020-01-28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.wildblueberries.com/blog/january-28th-is-national-blueberry-pancake-day/', NULL, NULL, 'About Blueberry Pancake Day', NULL, 'Blueberries are native to the United States, but they’ve only been part of the American diet for the past 100 years. Blueberries are packed with anti-oxidants, low in calorie and blend well with a number of different flavors including oats, salads and pancakes!\n\nBlueberry pancakes substitute blueberry syrup with whole blueberries for maple syrup, providing a feast for your senses in color, smell and taste. \n\nOr, blueberries can be baked inside the pancake batter for a tart and sweet treat. \n\nBlueberry Pancake Day is your excuse to enjoy this all American flapjack version of a breakfast favorite.', 'Unofficial Event: See National Berry Crops Initiative for topical info./ideas', 'National Berry Crops Initiative, Food First Marketing', '20481 Marval Place', 'Blodgett', 'OR', 'US', '97326', '(541) 456.2264', 'catmc@peak.org', 'Cat McKenzie, Public Relations', 'http://nationalberrycrops.org/index.php/contact-us/', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/_835IcXpLYg\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/uczOfr6cFy8\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/tWg_sb1nfRU\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '3636_12ways_blueberries.pdf', '3636_Basic Blueberry Recipes1.pdf', NULL, '12 Ways to Enjoy Blueberries', 'Great Blueberry Recipes', NULL, '<div style=\"clear:both\"><a href=\"http://www.blueberrycouncil.org/about-blueberries/history-of-blueberries/\"><img src=\"http://www.blueberrycouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/History-of-Blueberries-Infographic-WEB-VERSION.jpg\" title=\"History of Blueberries\" border=\"0\" /></a></div><div></div>', '3636_blueberry-infographic-a-handful-of-health.jpg', '3636_Just-Add-Blueberries-Infographic.jpg', 'History of Blueberries Infographic', 'Blueberry Nutrition Infographic', 'How to Add Blueberries to your Diet', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(216, 'Bobblehead Day, Ntl: January 7', 'United States', '1', '7', '2020', '2020-01-07', '1', '7', '2020', '2020-01-07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '45', '39', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.bobbleheadhall.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Bobblehead Day', NULL, 'First run in 2015, National Bobblehead Day is a celebration of this enduring German toy created in the 1700s based upon Asian (China and Japan) string dolls of the time. Their heads are extremely large and dance above small bodies, bobbing back and forth. Originally they were made of porcelain. Today, they\'re made of plastic. \n\nIn the 1990s these whimsical moving dolls entered sports marketing via Alexander Malcolm, who was simply looking for a promotional toy to market the San Francisco Giants. He produced over nearly 50 million of bobbleheads and built a global company that creates bobbleheads of various sports and cultural figures. Today many of these promotional items are coveted collectors items. ', 'National Bobblehead Hall of Fame and Museum', '170 S. 1st St. 2nd Floor', NULL, 'Milwaukee', 'WI', 'US', '53204', '(800) 414.1482', 'info@bobbleheadhall.com', 'General Information', 'https://www.bobbleheadhall.com/contact-us/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://twitter.com/BobbleheadHall', 'https://www.facebook.com/bobbleheadhall', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(217, 'Bodhi Day (B)(CN)(532 BC): January 13', 'China', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '6', '38', '61', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', ' ', 'http://familydharma.pulelehuadesign.com/bodhi.htm', 'Bodhi_Day_CNF.png', 'Bodhi_Day_CNE.png', 'About the Buddhist Holiday Bodhi Day', NULL, 'Bodhi Day celebrates the enlightenment of Siddhartha Gautama, the founder of Buddhism. Japan celebrates this event annually on December 8th. People following the Chinese religious calendar celebrate it on the 8th day of the 12th lunar (as apposed to Solar) month in the Chinese Calendar. \n\nThis day is the anniversary of him becoming the Buddha. \n\nA common misconception is that Siddhartha Gautama was born in India. He was born in Nepal, and the small Himalayan country takes great pride in this fact!', 'Buddhist Religious Calendar. See The Buddhist Association of the United States', 'Chuang Yen Monastery', '2020 Rte. 301', 'Carmel', 'NY', 'US', '10512', '(845) 225.1819  ', 'cym@baus.org', 'Visitor Services', 'http://www.baus.org/en/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '9070_Buddhism_infographic.jpg', '9070_bud.png', NULL, 'Understanding Buddhism, an Infographic', 'Buddhism 101 Infographic', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(218, 'Bonza Bottler Day™, Intl: January 1 ', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '44', '30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.bonzabottlerday.com', NULL, NULL, 'About Bonza Bottler Day', NULL, 'When the number of the month matches the number of the day, that\'s Bonza Bottler Day. Basically, it is a play on numbers. There are twelve Bonza Bottler Days a year.  \n\nThis event began in 1985. Bonza is Australian for \'Super\'. Bottler is slang for \'something excellent\'.', 'Bonza Bottler Day™', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '(864) 201.3988', 'bonza@bonzabottlerday.com', 'Gail Berger', 'http://www.bonzabottlerday.com/contact-us.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(219, 'Book Blitz Month, Ntl.: January ', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '58', '12', '8', '27', '52', ' ', 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://realbook.com/article/book-blitz-month', NULL, NULL, 'About National Book Blitz Month', NULL, 'January is National Book Blitz Month, a national campaign designed to promote reading and facilitate the relationship between authors and the media. \n\nLibraries often support the event by recommending their favorite books to curl up with. It is a great time for librarians, media specialists, and teachers to promote reading and introduce students to new authors. \n\nWays to celebrate include: \n\nCreating a mini-personal library; \n\nSetting a reading goal; \n\nCreating a reading list; \n\nSwapping books; \n\nFinding a reading buddy;\n\nJoining a book club.', 'Media 21', '7456 Evergreen Dr. ', NULL, 'Santa Barbara', 'CA', 'US', '93117', '(805) 680.9445', ' bgaughenmu@aol.com', 'Barbara Gaughen', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(220, 'Bootlegger\'s Day, Ntl.(1899/1920): January 17', 'United States', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '1', '8', '25', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.templetonrye.com/history/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Bootlegger\'s Day', NULL, 'Bootleggers are smugglers, sometimes distillers, who bring in alcoholic beverages where they are either taxed or prohibited. National Bootlegger\'s Day marks two distinct anniversaries on January 17th. \n\nThe birthday of bootlegger Al Capone: January 17, 1899\n18th Amendment (Prohibition) goes into effect: January 17, 1920\n\nThe term \'bootlegger\' refers to the flask smugglers used to hide in the top of their boots. In the age of the Old West, it was typically done to smuggle liquor to native Americans. With the advent of prohibition in the 1920s, it took on a whole new meaning.', 'Historical Anniversary.  No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(221, 'Braille Day, World (1809): January 4', 'Worldwide', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '13', '20', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'www.worldblindunion.org', NULL, NULL, 'About World Braille Day', NULL, 'Promoted by multiple organizations including the World Blind Union, World Braille Day celebrates the birth of Louis Braille on January 4, 1809. \n\nBraille was a Frenchman who lost his sight at a very early age. Braille learned to read using the Haüy system using Latin letters embossed on thick paper or leather. \n\nThe Haüy system was difficult and didn’t allow for writing. Frustrated with it, Braille came up with a new code when he was only 15 years old. This system of dots in small rectangular blocks was far easier to read by touch. More importantly, it allowed for writing. \n\nToday Braille’s original code exists in several variations that accommodate different languages. His new language revolutionized communication for millions of people and opened up a world of learning, opportunity and independence.', 'Historical Event.  See the World Blind Union (WBU) for more information.', '1929 Bayview Avenue', NULL, 'Toronto', 'ON', 'CA', 'M4G3E8', '(416) 486.9698', 'info@wbu.ngo', 'General Information', 'http://www.worldblindunion.org/English/contact-us/Pages/default.aspx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(222, 'Braille Literacy Month, Ntl. (1809): January ', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '13', '26', '52', NULL, ' ', 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://carroll.org/2015/01/january-national-braille-literacy-month/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Braille Literacy Month', NULL, 'January is the National Braille Literacy Month in the U.S. and it marks the anniversary of the birth of Louis Braille January 4, 1809. \n\nInventing the Braille code at the age of 15, Braille has changed the life of millions of people by giving those without sight the means to read and write. Even in today’s day and age of digital information, with audio books and recording Braille is used across the globe.\n\nNational Braille Literacy Month is supported by a number of organizations servicing the blind. ', 'Multiple Supporters. See Louis Braille School on topic. ', 'Louis Braille School', 'PO Box 704', 'Edmonds ', 'WA', 'US', '98020', '(425) 778.8428', 'http://louisbrailleschool.org/contact/', 'General Information', 'http://louisbrailleschool.org/contact/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(223, 'Break-up Day, Intl.: January 20', 'Worldwide', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '40', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2088787/Unhappy-new-year-January-worst-month-couples-thirds-broken-winter-blues.html', NULL, NULL, 'About International Break-up Day', NULL, 'International Break-up Day marks the single day each year when more romantic couples will split than on any other.  It is believed this may be because by January 20th, the holiday season has been over for three weeks and the next big stressor on relationships, Valentines Day, is still three weeks off. ', 'Statistical Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(224, 'Breckenridge Snow Sculpture Championships, Intl. (US-CO): January 20-29', 'United States', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', '1', '29', '2020', '2020-01-29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '22', '51', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.gobreck.com/events/international-snow-sculpture-championships', NULL, NULL, 'About the International Budweiser Snow Sculpture Championships', NULL, 'Organized by Breckenridge Brewery, the Breckenridge Snow Sculpture Championships is an annual event in which teams from across the world compete in sculpting giant figures from 20 tons of ice each. \n\nTaking place in Breckenridge, Colorado, the Budweiser Snow Sculpture Championships is a great event to spectate live, giving you the chance to both witness the amazing skill and speed of the sculptors, as well as to see the majestic works that they create.', 'Town of Breckenridge', '150 Ski Hill Road', 'PO Box 168', 'Breckenridge', 'CO', 'US', '80424', '(970) 547.4320', 'annettek@townofbreckenridge.com', 'Annette Kubek, Marketing & Administrative Coordinator', 'http://www.townofbreckenridge.com/index.aspx?page=228', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NP7Gbvv0i2o\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kVMhsoIiDlo\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/GoBreck/', 'https://www.instagram.com/gobreck/', 'https://twitter.com/GoBreck', ' Riverwalk Center, 150 West Adams Avenue, Breckenridge, CO 80424', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(225, 'Brexit Take 4: January 31', 'United Kingdom', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '18', '25', '36', '49', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'changes', 'One Year Only', 'https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/jun/20/not-just-uk-benefit-brexit-eu', 'BREXITF.png', 'BREXITE.png', 'About Brexit Implementation', NULL, 'Brexit Take IV? Yup! We thought this would be gone too, but the mess commonly known as Brexit is projected to continue into 2020 as deadline after deadline gets pushed back and Prime Ministers step down. We\'re not holding our breath for October 31, 2019 either. It finally happened on January 31, 2020. \n\n\"Should the United Kingdom remain a member of the European Union or leave the European Union?\"\n\nThis was the question asked of the British people in 2016 and the answer was leave.  This is the month the official divorce from Europe comes to fruition. \n\nThe European Union was created in 1958 and became an economic block in 1999 with the creation of the Euro.  The purpose of the European Union was to promote free trade, ease of movement and economic stability on the European continent. \n\nAdvantages are seen as maintaining sovereignty, limiting immigration of people from war zones and Eastern Europe, protecting British jobs, shoring up the power of the British parliament, and re-establishing Britain as an independent player on the world market.\n\nDisadvantages include loss of major industries as the relocate to Europe, reduced number of migrant workers, possible loss of security and foreign investment.', 'Political Event. See the British Government on Topic.', 'British Government Press Office', NULL, 'London', NULL, 'UK', NULL, '(+44)(0)2 07.276.7545', 'mediateam@cabinetoffice.gov.uk', 'Media Relations', 'https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/cabinet-office/about/media-enquiries', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, N