(263, 'Colonialism, 3rd Intl. Decade for the Eradication of Colonialism: 2011-2020', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2011', '2011-01-01', '12', '31', '2020', '2020-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '36', '20', '29', '59', NULL, NULL, 'Decade', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.un.org/en/decolonization/thirdinternatldecade.shtml', 'Decade_eradicate_ColonialismF.jpg', 'Decade_eradicate_ColonialismE.jpg', 'About the 3rd International Decade for the Eradication of Colonialism', NULL, 'Colonialism still exists to this day and over 4 million people in 17 “non-self-governing territories” across the globe still live under it. The top two current colonizers in the world are the United Kingdom with 10 colonies, followed by the United States and France with two each. \n\nColonialism is when one group of people moves into a land occupied by another group of people and proceeds to control it politically, militarily, economical and culturally.  \n\nPeoples whom continue under colonial rule include: Palestine (West Bank, Gaza and the Golan Heights); Western Sahara, Anguilla, Bermuda, British Virgin Islands, Cayman Islands, Falkland Islands, Montserrat, Saint Helena, Turks and Caicos Islands, United States Virgin Islands, Gibraltar, American Samoa, French Polynesia, Guam, New Caledonia, Pitcairn and Tokelau.', 'United Nations', 'Department of Public Information', ' ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10017', '(212) 963.7160', 'malu@un.org', 'Media Liaison', 'http://www.un.org/en/media/accreditation/contact.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
