(283, 'Dakar Rally (SA): Jan 5-17', 'Saudi Arabia', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '45', '47', '62', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'www.dakar.com', NULL, NULL, 'About the Dakar Rally', NULL, 'Dakar Rally began in Paris over forty years ago and continues annually. From 2020-2024 the rally will bee hosted in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.\n\nIts motto sums up the excitement of this car race: “A challenge for those who go.\"  \n\nThe Dakar Rally began when driver Thierry Sabine lost his way during the Abidjan-Nice Rally of 1977. His vision was to create a race that allowed the world to share scenery of the multi-day event. The race got its name from its first route beginning in in Paris, traveling through Algiers and finishing in the city of Dakar in Senegal. In 2009, due to security issues, the race moved to South America.', 'Amaury Sport Organisation', '42 Quai du Point du Jour', NULL, 'Boulogne Billancourt', NULL, 'FR', '92100', '(+33)(0)1 41.33.14.00', 'pressedakar@aso.fr', 'Media Relations', 'https://www.dakar.com/fr/espace-medias/identification-espace-medias', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AqBvApNe5SA\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
