(286, 'Day of Remembrance for the Victims of Nazism (DE)(1945): January 27', 'Germany', '1', '27', '2020', '2020-01-27', '1', '27', '2020', '2020-01-27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '59', '29', '16', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.history.com/news/auschwitz-liberation-soviets-holocaust', NULL, NULL, 'About Day of Remembrance for the Victims of Nazism in Germany', NULL, 'January 27, 1945, the Soviet Army liberated the infamous Auschwitz concentration camp in Poland. Each year since 1996, the nation of Germany has marked this anniversary as a day to remember all victims of National Socialism (Nazi), regardless of race, gender, sexual preference, political beliefs, or religion. ', 'Historical Anniversary. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(287, 'Day without a Scalpel, Ntl (1964): January 16', 'Worldwide', '1', '16', '2020', '2020-01-16', '1', '16', '2020', '2020-01-16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '20', '8', '43', '46', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC101126/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Day without a Scalpel', NULL, 'American surgeon, Charles Dotter performed the first angioplasty procedure on a leg, without a scalpel, in Portland Oregon on January 16, 1964. He changed how surgery could be done going forward. Day without a Scalpel occurs each year to honor his advancements to medical science. ', 'Historical Anniversary.  No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(288, 'Daylight Savings (FJ, TO), Ends: January 19', 'Fiji & Tonga', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '30', '4', ' ', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '3rd Sunday of January', 'http://www.worldtimezone.com/daylight.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Daylight Savings in Fiji & Tonga', NULL, 'Daylight Savings in Fiji & Tonga commences on the 1st Sunday of November (Spring Forward) and ends on the 3rd Sunday of January (Fall Back).\n\nOn this day we move the clock one hour ahead at 2AM in November or one hour back in January at 2AM in the morning on Sunday. \n\nThe saying, “spring forward, fall back” is a good way to remember. This works in the Northern and Southern Hemispheres as the seasons are reversed.\n\nBenjamin Franklin was the first to propose daylight savings time in 1784. Modern DST was established in 1895. Throughout history there were several variations ranging from 30 minutes to two hours. \n\nNot everyone observes DST, which can make setting appointments very challenging. The main purpose of DST is to make better use of daylight hours for farming, early morning activities (such as children walking to school in the light instead of dark) and saving energy. \n\nThe closer one lives to the North and South Pole, the longer the period of daylight in the summer months.  \n_______________________\n\nDaylight Savings Above the Equator:\n\nUnited Kingdom, Albania, Adorra, Austria, Bosnia, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Faroe Islands, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Greenland, Guernsey, Holy See, Hungary, Ireland, Isle of Man, Italy, Jersey, Kosovo, Latvia, Lebanon, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Macedonia, Malta, Moldova, Monaco, Montenegro, Morocco, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, San Marino, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Ukraine and Western Sahara: Last Sunday of March: Last Sunday October\n\nUnited States, Bahamas, Canada, Cuba, Saint Pierre & Miquelon: 2nd Sunday March; 1st Sunday of November\n\nIran: Begins March 21/22; Ends September 20/21\n\nIsrael & Palestine: Friday prior to last Sunday March; Last Sunday October\n\nJordan, Syria: Last Friday March; Last Friday October\n\nMexico: 1st Sunday April; Last Sunday October\n_______________________\n\nDaylight Savings Below the Equator:\n\nAustralia: 1st Sunday of October (Spring Forward ); 1st Sunday in April (Fall Back).\n\nBrazil: 3rd Sunday in October; 3rd Sunday in February.\n\nChile: 2nd Sunday in August and the 2nd Sunday in May.\n\nFiji & Tonga: 1st Sunday of November; 3rd Sunday of January.\n\nNamibia observes: 1st Sunday of September; 1st Sunday of April.\n\nNew Zealand: Last Sunday of September; 1st Sunday of April. \n\nParaguay: 1st Sunday of October; 4th Sunday of March.\n\nSamoa: Last Sunday of September; 1st Sunday of April.\n ', 'Natural Event. See the Benjamin Franklin Museum for History', 'Benjamin Franklin Museum', 'Independence National Historical Park\n143 South Third Street', 'Philadelphia', 'PA', 'US', '19106', '(215) 965.2305', 'http://www.nps.gov/common/utilities/sendmail/sendemail.cfm', 'General Information', 'http://www.nps.gov/inde/contacts.htm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(289, 'Dental Drill Day (1875): January 26', 'Worldwide', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '46', '20', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.historiccamera.com/cgi-bin/librarium2/pm.cgi?action=app_display&app=datasheet&app_id=2296', NULL, NULL, 'About Dental Drill Day', NULL, 'Today is the anniversary of the patenting of the electric dental drill by George F. Green from Kalamazoo on January 26, 1875.\n\nAlthough there were other patented dental drills prior to this, Green’s drill was the first one to be powered by an electromagnetic motor, making it unique to dentistry.', 'Historic Anniversary. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(290, 'Desertification, Decade for Deserts and the Fight Against Desertification: 2011- 2020', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2011', '2011-01-01', '12', '31', '2020', '2020-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '43', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', 'Decade', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://www.un.org/en/events/desertification_decade/', NULL, NULL, 'About the UN Decade for Deserts and the Fight Against Desertification', NULL, 'The United Nations General Assembly, by its resolution A/RES/62/195 of 2007, declared 2010 to 2020 the United Nations Decade for Deserts and the Fight Against Desertification (UNDDD).\n\nThe Assembly acknowledged the persistence of desertification, despite past and on-going global efforts, and a slow response to poverty eradication among drylands populations, and declared the Decade a period for concerted global action.\n\nThe resolution mandates the pursuit of three objectives, which are:\n\n1) Organizing activities to observe the Decade in order to raise awareness of (a) the causes of and (b) solutions to ongoing land degradation and desertification in the framework of the ten-year strategic plan and framework to enhance the implementation of the Convention (2008-2018);\n\n2) Mobilizing financial and technical support to the Convention secretariat, to support special initiatives in observance of the Decade as well as other observance events and activities worldwide; and\n\n3) Monitoring and reporting on progress in preparation of the Secretary General\'s Report to the General Assembly at its 69th Session on the status of implementation of the resolution.', 'United Nations', 'Department of Public Information', ' ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10017', '(212) 963.7160', 'malu@un.org', 'Media Liaison', 'http://www.un.org/en/media/accreditation/contact.shtml', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
(291, 'Diet Resolution Week: January 1-7', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '7', '2020', '2020-01-07', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '26', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.webmd.com/diet/5-diet-resolutions-new-year', NULL, NULL, 'About National Diet Resolution Week', NULL, 'The first seven days of each new year are considered “Diet Resolution Week\". It is an unofficial event with no sponsor, born of tradition. \n\nThese are the days of the year when, traditionally, people start the year off with their new diet and exercise regime.  Most people can stick with it a day or two, perhaps even seven.  Most don’t make it through the end of the month.  However, for the first seven days of the year, a lot of people are practicing and committed to their New Years Diet Resolution during this week.', 'Vegetarian Awareness Network', 'PO Box 321', ' ', 'Knoxville', 'TN', 'US', '37901', '(800) 328.8344', ' ', 'General Information', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
