(305, 'Ellis Island Day (1892): January 1', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '59', '48', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.libertyellisfoundation.org', NULL, NULL, 'About Ellis Island Day', NULL, 'Today marks the anniversary of the opening of Ellis Island on January 1, 1892.  \n\nEllis Island was the immigration gateway into the US on the East Coast in the late 19th Century through the mid 20th Century. Approximately 17,000,000 immigrants were admitted through Ellis Island between 1892 and 1954 when it closed. \n\nEllis Island was reopened in the fall of 1990 and remains one of the top tourist attractions in New York City. ', 'Historical Anniversary. See The Statue of Liberty-Ellis Island Foundation, Inc. on topic.', 'The Statue of Liberty-Ellis Island Foundation, Inc.', '17 Battery Place #210', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10004-3507', '(212) 561.4588', 'ContactUs@ellisisland.org', 'General Information', ' http://www.libertyellisfoundation.org/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:49', '2021-03-01 04:20:49'),
