(321, 'Festival of Sleep Day: January 3', 'United States', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '44', '52', NULL, NULL, ' ', 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.wikihow.com/Celebrate-the-Festival-of-Sleep-Day', NULL, NULL, 'About the Festival of Sleep Day', NULL, 'Now that Christmas is over and New Year\'s Eve is behind us, it is time to take a day (or a few hours) and get that well-deserved rest! Ergo the Festival of Sleep Day on January 3rd. Just before you have to jump back into your regular lifestyle, consider finding a person/pet or a stuffed animal to cuddle with. This is your day to sleep!', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(322, 'Fetish Day, Intl.: January 17', 'Worldwide', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '40', '44', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '3rd Friday January', 'http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2009/jan/16/civil-liberties-sexual-health', NULL, NULL, 'About International Fetish Day', NULL, 'The third Friday of January is International Fetish Day. This event was first celebrated in 2009 within the United Kingdom.  \n\nMerriam-Webster defines fetish as: \n\n	a:  An object (such as a small stone carving of an animal) believed to have magical power to protect or aid its owner; broadly :  a material object regarded with superstitious or extravagant trust or reverence\n\n	b:  An object of irrational reverence or obsessive devotion :  prepossession\n\n	c:  An object or bodily part whose real or fantasied presence is psychologically necessary for sexual gratification and that is an object of fixation to the extent that it may interfere with complete sexual expression\n\n2: A rite or cult of fetish worshippers\n\n3: Fixation \n\nSource: https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/fetish\n\nThe event does not have a sponsor.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(323, 'Fig Newton Day, Ntl.: January 16', 'United States', '1', '16', '2020', '2020-01-16', '1', '16', '2020', '2020-01-16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '46', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://inventors.about.com/od/fstartinventions/a/Fig_Newton.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About National Fig Newton Day', NULL, 'A Fig Newton is a soft cookie filled with fig jam. A machine invented in 1891 made the mass production of Fig Newtons possible. \n\nJames Henry Mitchell invented a machine which funneled the dough and jam into two separate channels which then produced an endless tube of dough encasing jam. This tube was cut into smaller pieces. The Kennedy Biscuit Works were the first company to use Mitchell\'s invention to mass-produce the cookies.\nOriginally called the Newton, the name was later changed to Fig Newton. The cookies were named after the Massachusetts town of Newton.', 'Mondelēz International', '100 Deforest Ave', NULL, 'East Hanover', 'NJ', 'US', '7936', '(855) 535.5648', 'http://www.mdlzcusthelp.com/feedbackform', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.snackworks.com/products/newtons', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(324, 'Financial Wellness Month: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '18', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://bestmoneymoves.com/blog/2017/01/04/how-to-help-your-employees-during-financial-wellness-month/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Financial Wellness Month', NULL, 'National Financial Wellness Month is observed in January each year and encourages people to set personal goals about their finances.  \n\nThere are currently over 196,000 personal financial advisers in the U.S., helping Americans reach their goals and turn that income into more net worth. With the ever-popular memes and jokes that the US educational system teaches students about everything except relevant and real-life solutions to problems, including how to deal with finances, this event is much-needed and gaining more and more popularity across the country.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(325, 'First Foot Day (UK): January 1', 'United Kingdom', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '17', '18', '1', '28', '49', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofScotland/The-History-of-Hogmanay/', NULL, NULL, 'About National First Foot Day in the United Kingdom', NULL, 'First Foot Day, Scottish in origin, celebrates the first-foot (the first dark haired gentlemen), to cross the threshold of a home on New Year’s Day. This person is seen as the bringer of good fortune for the coming year.  \n\nAccording to tradition not every first-foot can be the bringer of good fortune.  It is thought only a tall dark-haired gentleman can be the bringer of good luck.  \n\nAnd the fair-haired gentlemen among us?  Most believe them to bring very bad luck for the new year, though a few think it matters not.  \n\nHowever, all agree that a woman being the first-footer, the “ladies first” method of entering a room, is probably the worst thing you can do for luck by far. \n\nHey, it’s a custom.  It doesn’t have to make sense or be politically correct!', 'United Kingdom Tradition. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(326, 'Folic Acid Awareness Week, Ntl.: January 5-11', 'United States', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', '1', '11', '2020', '2020-01-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '26', '50', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', '2nd Week Jan', 'https://www.nbdpn.org/faaw.php', NULL, NULL, 'About National Folic Acid Awareness Week', NULL, 'National Folic Acid Awareness Week is an awareness campaign by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.\n\nFolic acid is a B-vitamin that is necessary for proper cell growth. If taken before and during early pregnancy, folic acid can prevent up to 70% of neural tube defects within the brain and spine. \n\nThe CDC and the U.S. Public Health Service recommend that all women between the ages of 15 and 45 consume 400 micrograms (mcg) of folic acid daily to prevent two types of neural tube defects, spina bifida and anencephaly. \n\nSince these birth defects develop within the first few weeks of pregnancy, it is important to have enough folic acid in your body BEFORE becoming pregnant and to continue getting enough folic acid during early pregnancy.  \n\nWomen need folic acid even if they are not planning to become pregnant as nearly half of all pregnancies in the United States are unplanned.', 'Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)', '1600 Clifton Road', NULL, 'Atlanta', 'GA', 'US', '30329-4027', '(800) 232.4636', 'https://wwwn.cdc.gov/dcs/ContactUs/Form', 'Media Relations', 'https://wwwn.cdc.gov/dcs/ContactUs/Form', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(327, 'Fort Worth Stock Show & Rodeo (US-TX): January 17 - February 8', 'United States', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', '2', '8', '2020', '2020-02-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '45', '18', '69', '52', NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://www.fwssr.com', NULL, NULL, 'About the Fort Worth Stock Show & Rodeo ', NULL, 'First held in 1896, the Fort Worth Stock Show and Rodeo is the original indoor extravaganza of carnival shows, entertainment, competitive riding and premium stock competitions. 45 acres under one roof. ', 'Fort Worth Stock Show & Rodeo', '3400 Burnett-Tandy Dr. ', NULL, 'Fort worth', 'TX', 'US', '76107', '(817) 877.2400', 'contact@fwssr.com', 'General Information', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(328, 'Free Thinker\'s Day (1737): January 29', 'United States', '1', '29', '2020', '2020-01-29', '1', '29', '2020', '2020-01-29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '8', '13', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.thomaspainesociety.org', NULL, NULL, 'About Free Thinker\'s Day', NULL, 'Freethinkers Day, also known as Thomas Paine Day, is an opportunity to promote appreciation of free thought in honor of the life and works of Thomas Paine. \n\nFree thought supports reason over faith, and rejects arbitrary authority. \nThomas Paine was a courageous freethinker whose work inspired great social and political advancement across world. \n\nRaised in England, Paine played a vital role in the American and French Revolutions. His books and pamphlets, including The Age of Reason, The Rights of Man, and Common Sense gained a mass audience for the liberating philosophy of the Enlightenment.\n \nIn the 1990s, the Truth-seeker magazine began celebrating Freethinkers Day on Thomas Paine\'s birthday  to educate the public on the importance of Thomas Paine in the history of freedom. Also in the 1990s, the Thomas Paine Foundation began celebrating the birthday of Thomas Paine on January 29th, a Thomas Paine Day proclamation on June 8 and other Paine theme events during the year.', 'Thomas Paine Society', '99 South Raymond Avenue', 'Suite B001', 'Pasadena', 'CA', 'US', '91105', '(626) 796.4529', ' ', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.thomaspainesociety.org/#!contact/czpl', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(329, 'Fresh Squeezed Juice Week, Ntl.: January 19-25', 'United States', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', '1', '25', '2020', '2020-01-25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '39', '8', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', '3rd Sunday in January', 'www.smoothiecentral.com', NULL, NULL, 'About the National Fresh Squeezed Juice Week', NULL, 'Fresh Squeezed Juice Week was created by the Juice and Smoothie Association (JASA) to educate consumers about the juice and smoothie industry, promote the juice bar franchises, and independent juice bars. ', 'Juice and Smoothie Association (JASA)', NULL, NULL, 'Chino Hills', 'CA', 'US', NULL, '(909) 597.0791', 'info@juicegallery.com', 'Dan Titus, Founder', 'http://www.juicegallery.com/about-juice-gallery/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(330, 'Fruitcake Toss Day: January 3', 'United States', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '45', '44', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TfCU38r44iE', NULL, NULL, 'About National Fruitcake Toss Day', NULL, 'This event was created as a joke, but has become a wonderful fundraising opportunity for charities.  It’s always newsworthy, and the dense consistency of fruitcakes makes them highly mobile when thrown.\n\nFruitcakes are a dessert, popular during Christmas. In some ancient cultures it was a custom to burry one\'s loved ones with fruitcake; today it is more customary to re-gift fruitcakes! Oh yes, most of us are guilty of this, or at least 38% of Americans report doing so.\n\nThose that re-gift have likely never tried a good fruitcake.  Many are marinated in brandy and make quite a delicious addition to afternoon tea.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Claxton Bakery for topical info.', 'Claxton Bakery, Inc.', '203 West Main Street', 'Claxton', 'GA', 'US', '30417', '(800) 841.4211', 'https://www.claxtonfruitcake.com/contact-form', 'Media Relations                                Media Relations', 'https://www.claxtonfruitcake.com/contact-form', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
