(376, 'J.R.R. Tolkien Day (1892): January 3', 'United Kingdom', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '58', '41', '49', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.tolkiensociety.org/author/biography/', NULL, NULL, 'About J.R.R. Tolkien Day', NULL, 'J.R.R. Tolkien was born on January 3, 1892 in Bloemfontein, South Africa.\n\nTolkien is universally accepted as the father of modern fantasy literature. The Lord of the Rings, The Hobbit and The Silmarillion are the Professor\'s most famous works. All are still read and loved all over the world.\n\nCelebrate on each January 3 at 9pm your time by raising a toast for the Professor.', 'Tolkien Society', '423 Bideford Green', NULL, 'Leighton Buzzard', ' ', 'UK', 'LU7 2TY', '(+44)(0)15.253.76339', 'https://www.tolkiensociety.org/contact/', 'General Information', 'https://www.tolkiensociety.org/contact/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(377, 'Jackson-Lee Day (Lee-Jackson Day): January 17', 'United States', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '36', '29', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Friday before MLK Day', 'https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/va-cities-and-counties-increasingly-want-to-make-lee-jackson-day-history/2018/01/11/adfea9d8-f23b-11e7-b390-a36dc3fa2842_story.html?noredirect=on&utm_term=.ff58b5f12fb5', NULL, NULL, 'About Lee-Jackson Day in Virginia', NULL, 'General Robert E Lee and General Thomas \'Stonewall\' Jackson were confederate officers during the American Civil War representing the South. Both are Virginia natives and both were born in the month of January, the 19th and 21st respectively. \n\nIn recent years there has been a noted backlash against all celebrations of the confederacy and its icons. Though once a state observed holiday in Virginia, increasingly counties and cities are bypassing it. With African Americans, particularly, the tying of this event to the National Martin Luther King holiday weekend, is insulting. Lee and Jackson were slave owners and fought to preserve slavery. Until 2000, the state celebrated all three men on the same day. ', 'Declared by the State of Virginia.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(378, 'Joygerm Day, Ntl: January 8', 'Worldwide', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '26', '17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://stilllearningsomethingnew.com/tag/joygerm-day/', NULL, NULL, 'About Joygerm Day', NULL, 'Created in in 1981 by Joan White, Joygerm Day is a play on words (Joy + Germ).  The holidays are over and it\'s time to \'infect the world with kindness, courtesy, civility, encouragement, respect and responsibility\', in other words, spread the joy. It is infectious!', 'Joygerms Unlimited', '448 Brattle Rd', NULL, 'Syracuse', 'NY', 'US', '13203', '(315) 472.2779', 'joygerms@gmail.com', 'Joan E White, Founder', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(379, 'Judgment Day: January 17', 'United States', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', '1', '17', '2020', '2020-01-17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '38', '25', '44', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.wellcat.com/january/judgment_day.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Judgment Day', NULL, 'It\'s Judgement Day. Don\'t panic! This Judgement Day is created by Wellcat.com, not the ethereal day of the same name before Saint Peter. \n\nBreathe.\n\nJudgement Day was created by the folks at Wellcat to remind us that we don\'t need to die to face judgement for our actions. Instead, use today to reflect on your own deeds and judge them accordingly. And after that - change what needs changing.', 'Wellcat Holidays', '2418 Long Lane', NULL, 'Lebanon', 'PA', 'US', '17046', '(717) 279.0184  ', 'info@wellcat.com', 'Thomas & Ruth Roy', 'http://www.wellcat.com/Order%20Information.htm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(380, 'Jumada al-Thani (M): January 26 - February 24', 'Worldwide', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', '2', '24', '2020', '2020-02-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '33', '38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jumada_al-thani', '5092_Jumada_al_ThaniF.jpg', '5092_Jumada_al_ThaniE.jpg', 'About the Muslim Month of Jumada al Thani', NULL, 'Jumada al-Thani is the sixth month of the Islamic calendar.  The Islamic Calendar year is a lunar calendar and is therefore 11-12 days shorter than the Gregorian calendar year.', 'Islamic Month, Religious Calendar', 'Islamic Society of North America', 'P.O. Box 38', 'Plainfield', 'IN', 'US', '46168', '(202) 544.5656 ', 'http://www.isna.net/contact.html', 'Public Relations', 'http://www.isna.net/contact.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(381, 'Kazoo Day, Ntl. (1852): January 28', 'United States', '1', '28', '2020', '2020-01-28', '1', '28', '2020', '2020-01-28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '32', '22', '12', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', ' ', 'http://www.nationalkazooday.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Kazoo Day', NULL, 'National Kazoo Day celebrates an instrument created during the nineteenth century in United States. \n\nCelebrated on January 28th (or on the fourth Thursday in January), National Kazoo Day was founded by Chaplin Willard Rahn of the Joyful Noise Kazoo Band located at the Homewood Retirement Home in Williamsport, Maryland. The campaign to make kazoo the national musical instrument of the United States continues to this day.\n\nThe Kazoo is an American musical instrument first developed in the 1840s and introduced to the world in 1852 by Alabama Vest and Thaddeus Von Clegg, a German clockmaker, during the Georgia State Fair. Known as the Down South Submarine, music is created by humming through the instrument. \n\nChanging the humming style of the musician changes the vibration. \n\nOn this day, kazoo enthusiasts would be delighted to know that kazoo can be purchased with discount. This is also the time when kazoo players meet up, play and share their music.', 'Kazoobie Kazoos. LLC ', '12 John Galt Road', NULL, 'Beaufort', 'SC', 'US', '29906', '(843) 982.6387', ' ', 'Stephen Murray, President ', 'http://www.nationalkazooday.com', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9rVxKEvqjPg\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(382, 'Keto Day, Ntl: January 5', 'United States', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '20', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-vitamin-shoppe-celebrates-second-annual-national-keto-day-in-support-of-the-keto-community-with-promotions-education-and-charitable-social-campaign-300980364.html', NULL, NULL, 'About National Keto Day', NULL, 'First held in 2019, National Keto Day serves to educate the public on the benefits of a low carb, high protein diet. Throughout the week of this event, National Keto Day sponsor The Vitamin Shoppe® holds a number of promotions and educational venues in store and online. ', 'The Vitamin Shoppe', '300 Harmon Meadow Blvd', NULL, 'Secaucus', 'NJ', 'US', '7094', '(201) 552.6000', 'https://www.vitaminshoppe.com/u/feedback.jsp', 'General Information', 'https://www.vitaminshoppe.com/u/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(383, 'Kiss a Ginger (Redhead) Day: January 12', 'Worldwide', '1', '12', '2020', '2020-01-12', '1', '12', '2020', '2020-01-12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '50', '28', '40', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://hotforginger.com/blog/international-kiss-a-ginger-day/', NULL, NULL, 'About Kiss a Ginger Day', NULL, 'International Kiss a Ginger Day began on Facebook in 2008 as a protest against a mean-spirited holiday urging people to kick redheads.  \n\nOnly 1.5% of the world’s population are natural redheads.  It is the rarest hair color on the planet for human beings (natural blond being the second at 2.5%).  \n\nThis is a grassroots supported event.', 'Global Personals Limited', 'Minton Place,\nVictoria Street', NULL, 'Windsor', NULL, 'UK', 'SL4 1EG', '(+44)(0)17 53.271.280', 'enquiries@hotfordating.com', 'Media Relations', 'http://hotforginger.com/contact-us/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(384, 'Kombucha \'Booch\' Day, Ntl: January 15', 'United States', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.kevita.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Kombucha Day', NULL, 'Kombucha or \'Booch\' is a fermented tea that has become to millennials what the martini is to the Great Generation and coolers to GenX. It\'s basically the \'it\' alcohol beverage. And like all things millennial, it\'s organic, has low cal options and includes various other things like herbs and probiotics, depending on flavor. Kombucha Day was first held in 2019.  ', 'KeVita', '6043 Olivas Park Drive Suite C', NULL, 'Ventura', 'CA', 'US', '93003', '(888) 310.6106', NULL, NULL, 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(385, 'Korean American Day (1903): January 13', 'United States', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '12', '61', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://keia.org/page/history-korean-american-day', NULL, NULL, 'About Korean American Day', NULL, 'Honoring the first 102 Korean immigrants to arrive in the United States on January 13, 1903; The US congress set aside this day beginning in 2005 with a resolution. \n\nThe Korea Economic Institute of America sponsors a highly anticipated luncheon in Washington DC each year, in honor of the anniversary. The day is celebrated by members of the Korean-American community throughout the United States. ', 'Korea Economic Institute ', '1800 K Street, NW Suite 300', NULL, 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20006', '(202) 464.1982', 'jg@keia.org', 'Yong Kwon, Director of Communications', 'http://keia.org/webform/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(386, 'Laba Festival (CN): January 2 ', 'China', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '15', '61', '69', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://www.travelchinaguide.com/essential/holidays/laba.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About China\'s Laba Festival', NULL, 'Originally, the celebration of the new harvest known as the Laba Festival was a national event in China and other Buddhist countries.\n\nWith the spread of Buddhism throughout the region, it became a day of celebration marking the enlightenment of Gautama Buddha at the age of 35.  This is the day the faith and Buddhist lifestyle. \n\nLaba congee, a porridge of several types of rice, beans, peanuts, dried fruit and lotus seeds, is the official dish of the day. Modern versions often incorporate tofu, potato and meat. ', 'National Festival. See China National Tourism Administration for info', 'China National Tourism Administration', '9A Jianguomennei Ave', 'Beijing', NULL, 'CN', '100740', '(+86)(10) 65.20.1114', 'webmaster@cnta.gov.cn ', 'Media Relations', 'http://en.cnta.gov.cn/about/Forms/AboutCnta/ContactUs.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(387, 'Law Enforcement Officers Appreciation Day, Ntl: January 9', 'United States', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '8', '29', '42', '25', '52', ' ', 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.concernsofpolicesurvivors.org/lead.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Law Enforcement Officers Appreciation Day', NULL, 'In light of recent negativity directed toward law enforcement nationally, there is a need to show law enforcement officers that our citizens recognize the difficult and sometimes impossible career they have chosen, in public service to us all.\n \nOn January 9th of each year we will call our nation’s citizens to action in support of law enforcement.  Those citizens who appreciate law enforcement and are discouraged about the negative attention being given to law enforcement are encouraged to take time on January 9, to show their support. \n\nThis event first ran in 2015.', 'C.O.P.S.', '846 Old South 5', NULL, 'Camdenton', 'MO', 'US', '65020', '(573) 346.4911', 'cops@nationalcops.org', 'General Information', 'https://www.concernsofpolicesurvivors.org/lead.html', '<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/149667365\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(388, 'Learn Your Name in Morse Code Day (1838): January 11', 'Worldwide', '1', '11', '2020', '2020-01-11', '1', '11', '2020', '2020-01-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '13', '29', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.brownielocks.com/learnyournameinmcday.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Learn Your Name In Morse Code Day', NULL, 'On January 11, 1838 Samuel Morse or Alfred Vail made their first public demonstration of the electric telegraph together. The purpose of this day is to increase interest in Morse Code, and help people learn about it. ', 'Brownielocks\' Holidays & Fun For Everyone', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'US ', NULL, NULL, 'b3b@ brownielocks.com', 'General Information', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(389, 'Leprosy Day, World: January 26', 'Worldwide', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Last Sunday January', 'https://www.lepra.org.uk/world-leprosy-day', NULL, NULL, 'About World Leprosy Day', NULL, 'World Leprosy Day takes place on the last Sunday in January. The day aims to raise awareness of a disease that many people believe extinct, when in fact around 210,000 new cases are diagnosed each year. The first documented case occurred near 600BC.\n\nThe last Sunday in January was chosen by French humanitarian Raoul Follereau in 1953, as the third Sunday from Epiphany from the Catholic calendar. The Catholic Church then reads the story of the Gospel where Jesus meets and heals a person with leprosy.', 'Lepra', '28 Middleborough', 'Colchester', 'Essex', NULL, 'UK', 'CO1 1TG', '(+44)(0)1 206.216.700', 'lepra@lepra.org.uk', 'General Information', 'https://www.lepra.org.uk/Pages/Contact.aspx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(390, 'Library Selfie Day: January 22', 'United States', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '58', '12', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '4th Wednesday in January', 'https://www.nypl.org/blog/2018/01/24/libraryshelfie-day-2018', NULL, NULL, 'About Library Selfie Day', NULL, 'Selfies are self-portraits taken with a cell phone, something quite difficult to do prior to 2008. It is inevitable then, that organizations would eventually tap into this trend and find ways to celebrate and promote their products and services. Library Selfie Day, created in 2014, encourages people to enter their local library and take a selfie with the books and other services offered, for posting on Social Media. Throughout the nation, thousands of public and private libraries hold special events on this day, including photography competitions for the best and most creative selfies.  Annually on the fourth Wednesday of January. ', 'New York Public Library', 'Stephen A. Schwarzman Building', 'Fifth Avenue & 42nd Street', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10018', '(212) 930.0736', 'amygeduldig@nypl.org', 'Amy Geduldig, Media', 'https://www.nypl.org/help/about-nypl/media-center', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(391, 'Life, Celebration of Life Day: January 22', 'United States', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '26', '20', '9', '17', '52', ' ', 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://foodforhealthinternational.com/celebration-of-life-month/', NULL, NULL, 'About Celebration of Life Day', NULL, 'Celebration of Life Day is a day set aside during Celebration of Life Month to focus specifically on the blessings brought to you by family, specifically children and grandchildren. The internet marks this day January 22.  The sponsor of it, Women of Freedom USA, marks it January 21.\n\nThere is a Celebrate Life Day occurring in June as well. That day, sponsored by Support Connections, honors cancer survivors and their families.', 'Women of Freedom USA', 'PO Box 493703', NULL, 'Redding', 'CA', 'US', '96049', NULL, 'womenoffreedom@aol.com', 'Judith Natale', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(392, 'Life, Celebration of Life Month: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '26', '9', '17', '52', NULL, ' ', 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://foodforhealthinternational.com/celebration-of-life-month/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Celebration of Life Month', NULL, 'Celebration of Life Month came about as a way to create an upbeat mood after the excitement of the holidays.  January can be a difficult month for many people.  In the Northern Hemisphere it is dark, cold often uneventful, (except for football championships).  This can leave people lonely. \n\nCelebration of Life Month seeks to remind people of all the things in their life that make it worth celebrating, whether your health or appreciating your children, grandchildren and spouse. ', 'Women of Freedom USA', 'PO Box 493703', NULL, 'Redding', 'CA', 'US', '96049', NULL, 'womenoffreedom@aol.com', 'Judith Natale', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(393, 'Life, Year of Life: 2020', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '12', '31', '2020', '2020-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '43', '13', '15', '2', NULL, NULL, 'Annual', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://blog.geolsoc.org.uk/2018/12/19/announcing-our-theme-for-2020-the-year-of-life/', NULL, NULL, 'About 2020, the Year of Life', NULL, 'Each year The Geological Society picks a theme and 2020 is the Year of Life. \n\nThroughout the year programs will explore life in a geoscience context through research conferences, lectures, education and other Society activities.\n\nTools are available from the organization for teachers and classrooms the world over. Topics include early life on planet earth, life in the depths of the oceans to the future of our planet and the possibility of life on Mars and other planets. Researchers, industry, economists and government bodies, as well as partner geoscience societies and organizations are all welcomed to get involved in this year long celebration of life.', 'Geological Society of London', 'Burlington House, Piccadilly, Mayfair', NULL, 'London', NULL, 'UK', 'W1J 0BD', '(+44) 20 74.34.9944', 'sarah.day@geolsoc.org.uk', 'Sarah Day', 'https://blog.geolsoc.org.uk/contact-us/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(394, 'Lohri (S)(H)(IN): January 13', 'India', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '57', '12', '69', '70', NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://www.indiatoday.in/lifestyle/culture/story/what-is-lohri-why-is-lohri-celebrated-sunder-mundriye-dulla-bhatti-punjabi-folklore-rabi-crop-952516-2016-01-13', NULL, NULL, 'About the Indian Festival of Lohri', NULL, 'Lohri is a cultural festival celebrated in the Punjabi region of India each year by the Sikhs and Hindus. It marks the end of the previous farming year and the financial beginning of the next farming year on the day following. It typically occurs on the 13th of January and features a large bonfire and several foods consumed during the festival including: gajjak, sarson da saag and makki di roti as well as a sweet rice mixed with jaggery and sesame seeds.', 'Indian Tradition. No Sponsor. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(395, 'Lughnasadh, South: January 31 - February 1', 'Southern Hemisphere', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', '2', '1', '2020', '2020-02-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '35', '38', '4', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', ' ', 'http://www.druidry.org/druid-way/teaching-and-practice/druid-festivals/lughnasadh/deeper-lughnasadh', '5262_LughnasadhF.png', '5262_LughnasadhE.png', 'About the Pagan Festival of Lughnasadh', NULL, 'Lughnasadh is a pagan festival celebrated during the peak of summer in August in the Northern Hemisphere and in February in the Southern Hemisphere. \n\nLughnasadh is Irish Gaelic for \"Commemoration of Lugh\" which can have two meanings, either marriage,  gathering of the crops or feast.  It is celebrated with feasting an dancing. In contemporary times the festival of Lughnasadh has grown to celebrate love and marriage as well. ', 'Order of the Bards, Ovaites & Druids', 'PO Box 1333', 'Lewes, East Sussex', 'London', ' ', 'UK', 'BN71DX', '(+44)(0)79 50.31.6218', 'adeoftheoldways@hotmail.co.uk', 'Adrian Rooke, Media Relations', 'http://www.druidry.org/about-us/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
