(398, 'Magh (S): January 13–February 11', 'Worldwide', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '2', '11', '2020', '2020-02-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '57', '38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.sikhiwiki.org/index.php/550', NULL, NULL, 'About the Sikh Month of Magh', NULL, 'In the Sikh religion, the month of Magh begins in January and lasts until mid-February in the Gregorian calendar. \n\nDuring the month of Magh, Sikhs celebrate the birth of several gurus in the faith: Bhai Himmat Singh on January 18, Baba Deep Singh on January 26, Guru Har Rai on January 31, and Sahibzada Ajit Singh on February 11.', 'Sikh Religious Month: See World Sikh Council for more details', 'World Sikh Council', 'PO Box 3635', 'Columbus', 'OH', 'US', '43210', '(888) 340.1702', 'contact@worldsikhcouncil.org', ' Media Relations', 'http://www.worldsikhcouncil.org/index.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(399, 'Magha (H): January 11-February 9', 'Worldwide', '1', '11', '2020', '2020-01-11', '2', '9', '2020', '2020-02-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Changes', ' ', 'http://www.bsswebsite.me.uk/Daysanddates/indiandate.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About the Hindu Month of Magha', NULL, 'Magha is the eleventh month of the Hindu calendar and corresponds to January-February in Gregorian calendar. It is called as such because the full moon is usually found nearby or within the Magha star cluster. \n\nMagha is a sacred month because at the beginning of the month the sun begins its northern path. \n\nMagha Purnima is the last and most important day of the month. It is regarded an auspicious day for holy baths. \n\nPLEASE NOTE: \nWe use the Indian Civil Calendar, which is the official holiday calendar in India, the largest Hindu nation.  The Hindu faith has many calendars, each specific to different regions and tribes with dates and celebrations marked by differing positions of the sun, moon and stars. Names of months and holidays, as well as the corresponding dates in the Gregorian Calendar, vary widely from one calendar to the next. Use our dates as a baseline. Find out which of the dozens of Hindu calendars is used in the region you live or plan to visit if you are looking to attend or witness a specific observance. ', 'Hindu Religious Holiday. See The Hindu Temple Society of North America for more information', 'New York Ganesh Temple', ' 45-57 Bowne Street', ' Flushing', 'NY', 'US', '11355', '(718) 460.8484 ', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', 'Media Relations', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(400, 'Makar Sankranti (H): January 15', 'Worldwide', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '38', '15', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Makar_Sankranti', 'Makar_SankrantiF.jpg', 'Makar_SankrantiE.jpg', 'About the Hindu day of Makar Sankranti', NULL, 'Makar Sankranti marks the transition of the Sun into the zodiac sign of Makara rashi (Capricorn) on its celestial path. The day is also believed to mark the arrival of spring in India. \n\nThis day is a solar event, making one it the few Indian festivals which fall on the same date in the Gregorian calendar every year: 14 January, with some exceptions when the festival is celebrated on 13 or 15 January due to leap years.\"\n\nPLEASE NOTE: \nWe use the Indian Civil Calendar, which is the official holiday calendar in India, the largest Hindu nation.  The Hindu faith has many calendars, each specific to different regions and tribes with dates and celebrations marked by differing positions of the sun, moon and stars. Names of months and holidays, as well as the corresponding dates in the Gregorian Calendar, vary widely from one calendar to the next. Use our dates as a baseline. Find out which of the dozens of Hindu calendars is used in the region you live or plan to visit if you are looking to attend or witness a specific observance. ', 'Hindu Religious Holiday. See The Hindu Temple Society of North America for more information', 'New York Ganesh Temple', ' 45-57 Bowne Street', ' Flushing', 'NY', 'US', '11355', '(718) 460.8484  ', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', 'Media Relations', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(401, 'Make Your Dream Come True Day: January 13', 'United States', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '18', '26', '8', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.internetworldstats.com/articles/art010.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Make Your Dream Come True Day', NULL, 'Make Your Dream Come True Day is the day to focus on the steps you need to take to make your dream come true. Nearly everything is possible if you’re willing to do the work to get it.  What do you really want? What do you need to do to get it? \n\nOkay. Now, go get it. \n\nThis is an unofficial event with no sponsor. ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(402, 'Male Watcher\'s Day: January 8', 'United States', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '28', '26', '44', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EnhCGrxCR-s&feature=relmfu', NULL, NULL, 'About National Male Watcher\'s Day', NULL, 'Today is a day to flip the tables on the cat calls and hoots. Male Watchers Day provides license to women to gawk, ogle and objectify men for a change (and see how they like being treated like a piece of meat). \n\nOkay, actually it is an excuse to indulge in a little eye-candy. And it is fun. Have a great day ladies!', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(403, 'Manuary™ (CA/US/UK): January', 'Canada, United States, United Kingdom', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '28', '7', '49', '52', NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://manuary.ca', NULL, NULL, 'About Manuary, the Month of Men', NULL, 'Established in 2010, Manuary™ is dedicated to raising funds to supporting cutting edge research and improving clinical care for patients suffering with head and neck cancer. Men are four times more likely to acquire this type of cancer. Support through the month is shown by allowing your beard to grow. That\'s right gentlemen, you have an excellent excuse not to shave for 31 days!\n\nThe ultimate goal of Manuary is to improve cure rates and quality of life for patients suffering with this disease.\n\nHead and neck cancer is the sixth most common cancer worldwide. Historically linked to tobacco and alcohol use, there are new found associations linking it to the human papilloma virus (HPV), which are on the rise.\n\nHead and neck cancers, as well as their treatment can have a profound negative impact on patient quality of life, as facial appearance, voice, breathing and swallowing can all be compromised. \n\nSurvival with contemporary treatment consisting of radiation, surgery and/or chemotherapy can be successful; however up to 50% of patients with advanced cancers die from the disease.', 'Manuary Canada', ' ', ' ', 'London', 'ON', 'CA', ' ', ' ', ' info@manuary.ca', 'General Information', ' https://manuary.ca/contact-us/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(404, 'March of Dimes Month (CA): January', 'Canada', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '9', '7', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.marchofdimes.ca/EN/news/2011/Pages/JanuaryisMarchofDimesMonth.aspx', NULL, NULL, 'About National March of Dimes Month in Canada', NULL, 'In Canada, January is also known as the March of Dimes Month. \n\nThe March of Dimes is a 65+ year old tradition of fundraising for Canadians with physical disabilities. \n\nDuring January, many Canadians put on their warmest clothes and go against the winter cold, canvassing door-to-door to raise funds for the March of Dime\'s events and programs, working tirelessly to help those in need.', 'March of Dimes', '10 Overlea Blvd.', NULL, 'Toronto', 'ON', 'CA', 'M4H 1A4', '(416) 425.3463 ', 'http://www.marchofdimes.ca/E boutUs/Pages/ContactUs.aspx', 'General Information', 'http://www.marchofdimes.ca/E boutUs/Pages/ContactUs.aspx', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(405, 'Martin Luther King Holiday: January 20', 'United States', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '36', '25', '59', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '3rd Monday of January', 'www.thekingcenter.org', NULL, NULL, 'About the National Martin Luther King Holiday in the United States', NULL, 'Martin Luther King Holiday was first organized in 1986 to celebrate the civil rights leader\'s life and great contributions to western society. He was born January 15, 1929 in Atlanta, Georgia. The national holiday moves to allow for a three-day weekend in the United States. \n\nDr. Martin Luther King was an American pastor who rose to prominence in the 1950s as a voice for social justice and equal rights.  His distinctive auditory style galvanized an entire movement and played a key role in the 1964 Civil Rights act, which made the discrimination of persons based upon race, ethnicity, origin, religion or sex, a crime. He is considered one of the most influential people of the 20th Century.\n\nDr. King was assassinated on April 4, 1968 in Memphis, Tennessee.', 'National Holiday. See The King Center,', 'The King Center', ' 449 Auburn Avenue, NE', 'Atlanta', 'GA', 'US', '30312', '(404) 526.8900', 'http://www.thekingcenter.org/contact-us', 'General Information', ' http://www.thekingcenter.org/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(406, 'Martin Luther King\'s Birthday (1929): January 15', 'United States', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '36', '25', '59', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'www.thekingcenter.org', NULL, NULL, 'About Dr. Martin Luther King\'s Birthday', NULL, 'Dr. Martin Luther King was an American pastor who rose to prominence in the 1950s as a voice for social justice and equal rights.  Today is his actual birthday, January 15, 1929.  The annual holiday in his honor is celebrated in the US on the Monday closest to this date.\n\nKing’s distinctive auditory style galvanized an entire movement and played a key role in the 1964 Civil Rights act, which made the discrimination of persons based upon race, ethnicity, origin, religion or sex, a crime. He is considered one of the most influential people of the 20th Century.\n\nDr. King was assassinated for his efforts on April 4, 1968 in Memphis, Tennessee. He was only 39 years old.', ' Historic Anniversary. No Sponsor. See The King Center,', 'The King Center', ' 449 Auburn Avenue, NE', 'Atlanta', 'GA', 'US', '30312', '(404) 526.8900', 'http://www.thekingcenter.org/contact-us', 'General Information', ' http://www.thekingcenter.org/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(407, 'Martyrs Day (AZ)(1990): January 20', 'Azerbaijan', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '29', '62', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://mod.gov.az/en/the-january-20-tragedy-414/', NULL, NULL, 'About Martyrs Day in Azerbaijan', NULL, 'Martyrs Day is a national holiday in Azerbaijan, honoring the sacrifice of the Azeris. Ultimately, 131 civilians killed by troops and 744 injured over several days by the Soviet Union beginning January 20, 1990. The event is referred to as Black January. The country declared and gained its independence in 1991.', 'Historical Anniversary. National Holiday Azerbaijan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(408, 'Martyrs Day (PA)(1964): January 9', 'Panama', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '59', '12', '34', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.panamatoday.com/panama/martyrs-day-panama-6077', NULL, NULL, 'About Martyrs Day in Panama.', NULL, 'On January 9, 1964, Panamanians rose up against America sovereignty over the Panama Canal Zone. Over 3 days of fighting, with students against the US military, 22 Panamanians and 4 US soldiers were killed. Today is a national day of remembrance in Panama called Día de los Mártires. ', 'Historical Event. Panama Official Holiday. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(409, 'Marzipan Day, Ntl.: January 12', 'United States', '1', '12', '2020', '2020-01-12', '1', '12', '2020', '2020-01-12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.cooksinfo.com/marzipan-day', NULL, NULL, 'About National Marzipan Day', NULL, 'Marzipan is a candy made from almond meal and sugar, which is believed to have originated in Persia. The thick consistency of marzipan, and its ability to take coloring, makes it perfect for sculpting. It is often used to create intricate decoration on cakes or eaten on its own.\n\nMarzipan Day is an unofficial event with no sponsor.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Retail Confectioners Intl. for info on subject.', 'Retail Confectioners International', '2053 S Waverly Ave, Ste C', 'Springfield', 'MO', 'US', '65804', '(800) 545.5381', 'info@retailconfectioners.org', 'Denise Alvarez Marketing Manager', 'http://www.retailconfectioners.org/?page=staff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(410, 'Mauni Amavasya (H): January 24', 'Worldwide', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '38', '20', '12', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.hindu-blog.com/2009/01/mauni-amavasi-mauna-amavasya-vow-of.html', 'Mauni_AmavasF.jpg', 'Mauni_AmavasE.jpg', 'About the Hindu Day of Mauni Amavasya', NULL, 'Mauni Amavas (Mauni Amavasya) commemorates of the birthday of Manu Rishi in the Hindu faith. Rituals include bathing in holy rivers to promote prosperity. A Maun (silent) Vrat is observed on this day to quiet all senses. Homas, giving to charity and meditation are other activities performed, which are believed to remove sins and vanquish enemies.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: \nWe use the Indian Civil Calendar, which is the official holiday calendar in India, the largest Hindu nation.  The Hindu faith has many calendars, each specific to different regions and tribes with dates and celebrations marked by differing positions of the sun, moon and stars. Names of months and holidays, as well as the corresponding dates in the Gregorian Calendar, vary widely from one calendar to the next. Use our dates as a baseline. Find out which of the dozens of Hindu calendars is used in the region you live or plan to visit if you are looking to attend or witness a specific observance. ', 'Hindu Religious Holiday. See The Hindu Temple Society of North America for more information', 'New York Ganesh Temple', ' 45-57 Bowne Street', ' Flushing', 'NY', 'US', '11355', '(718) 460.8484  ', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', 'Media Relations', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(411, 'Measure Your Feet Day: January 23', 'United States', '1', '23', '2020', '2020-01-23', '1', '23', '2020', '2020-01-23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '46', '9', '39', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://brannock.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Measure Your Feet Day', NULL, 'Measure Your Feet Day commemorates how we measure feet, though why it is not on the birthday (May 16, 1903) of the device’s inventor or the day patent  US1682366 was approved (August 28, 1928) or filed (November 4, 1925), or even his death (November 22, 1992) is unknown. There seems to be nothing significant about this date, historically. \n\nThe Brannock Device® was revolutionary, simple to use and increased the wear and comfort of shoes. The device was invented by Charles F. Brannock as a way to attract more customers to his store.  The US Army took notice in the 1940s and it became the standard for determining shoe size and fit.  We still use his invention today.\n\nBrannock was inducted into the Inventor’s Hall of Fame in 2007. ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Brandock Device Company for topical info. ', 'Brandock Device Company', '116 Luther Ave.', 'Liverpool', 'NY', 'US', '13088', '(315) 475.9862', 'https://brannock.com/pages/contact', 'General Information', 'https://brannock.com/pages/contact', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(412, 'Meitlisunntig (CH): January 12', 'Switzerland', '1', '12', '2020', '2020-01-12', '1', '12', '2020', '2020-01-12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '29', '50', '69', '16', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '2nd Sunday of January', 'https://www.britannica.com/event/Toggenburg-Succession', NULL, NULL, 'About Switzerland\'s Meitlisunntig ', NULL, 'During the Villmergen War of 1712, the women of the townships of Meisterschwaden and Fahrwangen Switzerland paraded to the frontlines to assist the men fighting. Each year in honor of this event, the young women of both towns dress in period costume and participate in a military parade before a female General Staff. Upon completion, a festival is held. ', 'Swiss Custom', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(413, 'Memento Mori (Mortality Day): January 3', 'United States', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', '1', '3', '2020', '2020-01-03', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '44', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.wellcat.com/winter.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About National Memento Mori or Mortality Day', NULL, 'This is not a fun holiday, but an important one.\n\nMemento Mori, or Mortality Day, is a day to remind us of our own mortality and the unavoidable fact that one day each and everyone of us will all die. It\'s always important for a person to keep that in mind, not to scare him/herself, but to simply be mindful of how short life actually is and how important it is to spend our time well. Today is about evaluating your life and legacy, then making adjustments where needed.', 'Wellcat Holidays', '2418 Long Lane', NULL, 'Lebanon', 'PA', 'US', '17046', '(717) 279.0184  ', 'info@wellcat.com', 'Thomas & Ruth Roy', 'http://www.wellcat.com/Order%20Information.htm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50');
