(422, 'Moon-Full: January 10', 'Worldwide', '1', '10', '2020', '2020-01-10', '1', '10', '2020', '2020-01-10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '43', '31', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://lunaf.com/lunar-calendar/2019', '5495_Full_MoonF.jpg', '5495_Full_MoonE.jpg', 'About the January Full Moon', NULL, 'January’s full moon is known as the Wolf Moon or Long Nights Moon. The full moon occurs when the Moon is completely illuminated by the sun. It is on the opposite side of the earth from the sun, an ecliptic longitude of 180 degrees.', 'Natural Event. No Sponsor. See American Astronomical Society for info. ', 'American Astronomical Society', '2000 Florida Ave., NW, Suite 300', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20009-1231', '(202) 328.2010', 'aas@aas.org', 'Media Relations', 'https://aas.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(423, 'Moon-New: January 24', 'Worldwide', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '43', '31', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://lunaf.com/lunar-calendar/2019', 'NewMoonF.jpg', 'NewMoonE.jpg', 'About the April New Moon', NULL, 'The New Moon occurs when the Moon and the Sun have the same elliptical longitude. This happens when the moon is at its closest point to the sun in its orbit. From earth we usually cannot see it. The New Moon is considered the first phase. ', 'Natural Event. No Sponsor. See American Astronomical Society for info. ', 'American Astronomical Society', '2000 Florida Ave., NW, Suite 300', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20009-1231', '(202) 328.2010', 'aas@aas.org', 'Media Relations', 'https://aas.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(424, 'Mulberry Street (1937): January 24', 'United States', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '9', '13', '58', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.seussville.com/', NULL, NULL, 'About Mulberry Street Day in Honor of Dr. Seuss', NULL, 'Today is the anniversary of the publishing of Theodor Seuss Geisel’s (Dr. Seuss) first book “And to Think That I Saw It on Mulberry Street”, January 24, 1937. \n\nDr. Seuss has sold 600 million copies of his 44 children\'s books, each and every one of them - a classic. He is one of the most successful authors and illustrators of all time.', 'Historical Anniversary. Random House Children\'s Books on topic.', 'Random House Children\'s Books', '1745 Broadway', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10019', '(212) 782.9000', 'rhkidspublicity@randomhouse.com', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/media-queries/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(425, 'Multicultural Children\'s Book Day: January 31', 'United States', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '58', '12', '9', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Last Friday in January', 'http://www.cbcdiversity.com/post/169470797788/multicultural-childrens-book-day-2018', NULL, NULL, 'About Multicultural Children’s Book Day', NULL, 'Multicultural Children’s Book Day,  a national non-profit, created to raise awareness around diversity in children’s literature so that all kids can see themselves in books.  The mission of the Multicultural Children’s Book Day is to put diverse children’s books on shelves and into the hands of children and families across the country. This event first ran in 2014.', 'CBC Diversity/The Children’s Book Council', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'US', NULL, '(917) 215.1779', 'sara@orangejuicecom.com', 'Sara Sinek- Toborowsky ', 'http://www.cbcdiversity.com/post/169470797788/multicultural-childrens-book-day-2018', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(426, 'Mummers Parade, Philadelphia (US-PA): January 1', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '32', '69', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.visitphilly.com/things-to-do/events/the-mummers-parade/', 'MummersParadeF.png', 'MummersParadeE.png', 'About the Mummers Parade in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania', NULL, 'Attracting over 100,000 people each year this 120-year-old+ tradition features over 10,000 men, women and children dressed in ostentatious costumes twirling, sashaying, pirouetting and strutting down the city’s main streets.\n\nMummers are men and women of all ages who belong to more than 40 organized clubs that make up the parade participants.\n\nThe clubs, split into five categories — Comics, Wench Brigades, Fancies, String Bands and the Fancy Brigades — function mainly to stage their playful performances on New Year’s Day and at other events throughout the year. Mummery is a Philadelphia tradition spanning generations and originated in ancient Rome. Then laborers celebrated Saturnalia by marching in masks,  exchanging gifts and making light of the issues of the day.\n\nRead more at: https://www.visitphilly.com/things-to-do/events/the-mummers-parade/', 'Freedom of Information, LLC.', 'PO Box 597', NULL, 'Moorestown', 'NJ', 'US', '8057', NULL, 'whois716@foi.com', 'General Information', 'http://mummers.com', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/eZuf6CiTw6E\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6s0WSBAXM9c\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Bwsbkbx6vq0\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,