(443, 'Opposites Day: January 25', 'United States', '1', '25', '2020', '2020-01-25', '1', '25', '2020', '2020-01-25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '13', '44', '9', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opposite_Day', NULL, NULL, 'About Opposites Day', NULL, 'Opposites Day is celebrated on January 25 in the United States. It’s a day about not saying what you mean or meaning what you say.  In other words, if it is hot outside, you would say the opposite: it is cold. It’s a fun day for kids, but could get adults in a lot of trouble.  Practice at your own risk!', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
