(462, 'Peking Duck Day, Ntl.: January 18', 'United States', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '61', '52', ' ', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.pilotguides.com/articles/a-cultural-classic-peking-duck/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Peking Duck Day', NULL, 'Peking Duck (Roast Duck), a dish originating in Beijing (formerly called Peking) China, could be considered a diplomatic dish. It was served to then Secretary of State Henry Kissinger on July 10, 1971. He immediately fell in love with the dish and it marked the beginning of US/China relations. \n\nThe delicacy first appeared during the Yuan Dynasty under Kublai Khan (1279–1368 AD), and was popularized during the Ming Dynasty (1368 to 1644 AD) through the imperial court. ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(463, 'Penguin Day, Ntl.: January 20', 'United States', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', '1', '20', '2020', '2020-01-20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.boredpanda.com/penguin-awareness-day-photography/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Penguin Day', NULL, 'National Penguin Day in the United States raises awareness of their plight, especially several species of penguins that are threatened by climate change. There are 17 different species of penguins, all native to the Southern Hemisphere.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See SANCCOB on topic.', 'SANCCOB', '22 Pentz Drive\nTable View', 'Cape Town', NULL, 'ZA', '7441', '(+27)(0)2 1.557.6155', 'info@sanccob.co.za', 'General Information', 'http://sanccob.co.za/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(464, 'Perihelion Day: January 5', 'Worldwide', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '43', '15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perihelion_and_aphelion', NULL, NULL, 'About the Day the Earth is Closest to the sun, Perihelion Day', NULL, 'Perihelion Day is the day of the year when the Earth is closest to the Sun. \n\nThis day changes from year-to-year, but it\'s usually in early January. \n\nThe world \"perihelion\" comes from the Ancient Greek words \"peri\" meaning \"near\" or \"close\", and \"helios\" which translates to \"the Sun\". \n\nPerihelion is the opposite of Aphelion, when the Earth is at its furthest point from the Sun. \"Apo\" means \"away, off, apart\".', 'Natural Event. Gravity organizes Perihelion.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(465, 'Personal Self-defense Awareness Month, Ntl: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '42', '45', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.nsdi.org/about.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About National Pesonal Self-defense Awareness Month', NULL, 'A promotion of the SAFE program for women and teenage girls, National Personal Self-defense Awareness Month focuses on teaching awareness and risk avoidance in addition to defensive tactics that can save lives. ', 'National Self-defense Institute, Inc.', 'PO Box 398355', NULL, 'Miami Beach', 'FL', 'US', '33239', '(305) 868.6734', 'nsdi@att.net', 'General Information', 'http://www.nsdi.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(466, 'Personal Trainer Awareness Day: January 2', 'United States', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '45', '26', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.prweb.com/releases/2005/12/prweb319979.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Personal Trainer Awareness Day', NULL, 'Personal Trainer Awareness Day coincides with the majority of us making New Year\'s resolutions to get in shape and exercise. \n\nFrom their 2005 press release on the day:\n\nPONTE VEDRA BEACH, FLORIDA (PRWEB) DECEMBER 9, 2005\nThe co-founders of January 2nd\'s National Personal Trainer Appreciation Day, Jim Labadie and Joey Atlas, know the holidays can be a calorically challenging time of year. To avoid putting on extra weight this season, they advocate starting a fitness plan before the festivities begin.\n\nMost people realize getting more physical activity and eating a nutritious diet of small, frequent and nutritious meals six days a week is critical to keeping weight off. However, to keep ones sanity, especially around the holidays, it\'s a good idea for people to give themselves one \"\"cheat\"\" or \"guilt-free\" day per week.\n\nAtlas explains, \"The \'guilt-free\' day should be one day out of the week when you allow yourself to eat anything you really, really want. During the holidays it is a good idea to have your guilt-free day on either Christmas Eve or Christmas Day, for example. At the same time it\'s important to understand the splurging must be limited to that one day. Behaving yourself at other holiday functions, such as office parties, will be made easier knowing your day is coming.\"\n\nOther tips include:\n1-Walking extra laps around the mall when shopping.\n\n2-Taking a 10-minute walk after a large holiday meal to burn calories and improve digestion.\n\n3-Limiting alcohol consumption due to the fact it often leads to making poor food choices.\n\n4-Writing down fitness goals and sticking to them.\n\n5-Having a clear picture in your mind of how great you\'re going to feel after the holidays having kept the weight off.\n\nThe website no longer exists for this event and it is currently unsponsored.\"\n ', 'Currently Unsponsored. See the National Exercise Trainers Association on topic', 'National Exercise Trainers Association', '12800 Industrial Park Blvd. Ste. 220', 'Minneapolis', 'MN', 'US', '55441–3929 ', '(763) 545.2505', 'http://netafit.org/contact.php', 'Media Relations', 'http://netafit.org/contact.php ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(467, 'Pet Travel Safety Day, Ntl.: January 2', 'United States', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '48', '42', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.pettravelsafetyday.com/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Pet Travel Safety Day', NULL, 'National Pet Travel Safety Day might sound like a redundant holiday, but it addresses a serious issue.\n\nUnfortunately, statistics show that for too many pet owners, including most of those whom believe they are doing everything right, pet travel safety is a mystery. \n\nAnd the real bad news? \n\nPets pay the price of our ignorance. Take some time during this day to read, think and talk about your pet\'s safety when traveling.  They will thank you later!', 'Colleen Paige', '14747 N Northsight Blvd ', 'Suite 111, PMB 309', 'Scottsdale', 'AZ', 'US', '85260', '(480) 624.2599', 'pr@theholidayguild.com', 'Colleen Paige', 'http://www.colleenpaige.com/holidays', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
