(472, 'Plant Health, 2020 Intl. Year of: 2020 ', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '12', '31', '2020', '2020-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '20', '43', '19', NULL, NULL, 'Annual', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://undocs.org/A/RES/73/252', NULL, NULL, 'About 2020 International Year of Plant Health', NULL, 'Plants form the foundation for all life on Earth. They create ecosystem functions and food security, clean the air, keep hillsides in place, provide shelter, safety and joy. The health of plants is as essential to feeding the world as it is to allowing it to breathe and prosper. \n\nThe United Nations declares 2020 as the Year of Plant Health and will focus on a variety of issues including protecting the environment, forests and biodiversity from plant pests; addressing the effects of climate change on plants and ecosystems as well as supporting efforts to end hunger, malnutrition and poverty.', 'United Nations', 'Department of Public Information', ' ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10017', '(212) 963.7160', 'malu@un.org', 'Media Liaison', 'http://www.un.org/en/media/accreditation/contact.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(473, 'Play God Day: January 9', 'United States', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '38', '35', '44', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://themommygamers.com/2014/01/play-god-day-january-9th/', NULL, NULL, 'About Play God Day', NULL, 'Play God Day is based on the idea of playing God. \n\nHowever, while \"playing God\" is a phrase that usually has a negative connotation and can be considered blasphemous in many faiths, in this case it\'s meant to encourage people to think what would they do if they had the power of a god. What would they do for humanity? How would they help people? \n\nOnce you have an idea of what you would do, find a way to make it happen, even if it’s something as simple as holding the door.  \n\nThis is an unofficial holiday with no sponsor.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(474, 'Plough Monday (UK): January 13', 'United Kingdom', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '15', '8', '10', '49', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Monday following January 6', 'http://projectbritain.com/ploughMonday.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Plough Monday in the United Kingdom', NULL, 'Epiphany has passed, closing out the Twelve days of Christmas for another year. On the Monday following Epiphany, it\'s back to work and time to plow the fields for this year\'s crop. Ploughs are blessed. Parades are held and England\'s farmers go back to work. ', 'British Custom. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(475, 'Poetry at Work Day: January 14', 'Worldwide', '1', '14', '2020', '2020-01-14', '1', '14', '2020', '2020-01-14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '58', '8', '12', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '2nd Tuesday January', 'https://www.tweetspeakpoetry.com/poetry-at-work-day/', NULL, NULL, 'About Poetry at Work Day', NULL, 'Poetry at Work Day seeks to promote creativity in the office and spread a little culture and cheer post holidays. Celebrating is as simple as posting your favorite poem on the wall, or leaving a copy in the lunch room. \n\nSee the Tweetspeak website for ideas, poems and templates. ', 'Tweetspeak Poetry', '1872 Pleasantville Rd, Ste. 123', NULL, 'Briarcliff', 'NY', 'US', '10510', '(914) 944.9036', 'email@tspoetry.com', 'General Information', 'http://www.tweetspeakpoetry.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(476, 'Polka Dot Day, Ntl.: January 22', 'United States', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.usmagazine.com/stylish/news/celebrate-national-polka-dot-day-with-hollywood-icon-minnie-mouse-w461307/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Polka Dot Day', NULL, 'National Polka Dot Day celebrates the fabric pattern of dots on a solid background. \n\nThe term ‘polka dot’ first appeared in Godey’s Lady’s Book in 1857 describing the pattern on a muslin scarf as “for light summer wear, surrounded by a scalloped edge, embroidered in rows of round polka dots.”\n\nThe word \'polka\' is a descriptor for Polish women. The pattern of dots on fabric hit its height in the 1930s and 1940s following its debut on Minnie Mouse\'s dress in 1926. Other popular culture references to the pattern include Marilyn Monroe\'s 1951 bikini, The song by Brian Hyland \"Its Bitsy Teenie Weenie Yellow Polka Dot Bikini\" and the Marvel comic hero Polka Dot Man.\n\nFor more on the history of polka dots see: https://www.thehairpin.com/2013/06/a-brief-history-of-polka-dots/', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(477, 'Polka Month, Ntl.: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '32', '22', '45', '12', '52', NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.ipapolkas.com/blog/2016/12/2017-i-p-a-january-polka-month-dance-texas/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Polka Month', NULL, 'This Bohemian dance, the polka, originated in the early nineteenth century in today’s Czech Republic. It is rumored a teenager by the name of Anna Slezak invented it in 1834.  The simple, vivacious dance quickly spread to Prague’s ballrooms and when it was perform on stage at the Odeon Theater, Paris in 1840, it became an international sensation.\n\nThe word ‘pulka’ in Czech means ‘half-step’. \n\nNational Polka Month is focused on keeping this folk dance and its music alive, as well as introducing it to new generations. ', 'International Polka Association', '4608 S. Archer Ave.', NULL, 'Chicago', 'IL', 'US', '60632', '(800) 657. 6552', 'ipapolkas@gmail.com', 'General Information', 'http://www.ipapolkas.com/contact-the-ipa/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(478, 'Pongal (H): January 15-18', 'Worldwide', '1', '15', '2020', '2020-01-15', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '38', '15', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_Pongal', 'PongalF.jpg', 'PongalE.jpg', 'About the Hindu Day of Pongal', NULL, 'Pongal is a Hindu festival marking the beginning of the end of winter and corresponds to the time when the sun is moving towards Uttarayanam (north) from Dakshinayanam (south). \n\nUsually, Pongal is celebrated on or near the 14th of January. On this day, people clean their houses, wear new clothes and exchange gifts. Rituals include chewing on sugar cane and decorate the houses with kolam, which is made using rice paste in different colors.\n\nPongal is the harvest festival of South India and most notably celebrated in the southern state of Tamilnadu.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: \n\nWe use the Indian Civil Calendar, which is the official holiday calendar in India, the largest Hindu nation.  The Hindu faith has many calendars, each specific to different regions and tribes with dates and celebrations marked by differing positions of the sun, moon and stars. Names of months and holidays, as well as the corresponding dates in the Gregorian Calendar, vary widely from one calendar to the next. Use our dates as a baseline. Find out which of the dozens of Hindu calendars is used in the region you live or plan to visit if you are looking to attend or witness a specific observance. ', 'Hindu Religious Holiday. See The Hindu Temple Society of North America for more information', 'New York Ganesh Temple', ' 45-57 Bowne Street', ' Flushing', 'NY', 'US', '11355', '(718) 460.8484  ', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', 'Media Relations', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(479, 'Pop Music Chart Day (1936): January 4', 'United States', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '32', '14', '12', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.billboard.com/archive/charts', NULL, NULL, 'About Pop Music Chart Day', NULL, 'Pop Music Chart Day marks the anniversary of Billboard magazine\'s publishing of its first music hit parade, or chart of the most popular songs on January 4, 1936.  This day marks the advent of ‘pop’ or ‘popular’ music. ', 'Historical Anniversary.   See Billboard Magazine. ', 'Billboard Magazine', '770 Broadway', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10003', '(845) 267.3007 ', 'conferences@billboard.com ', 'Customer Service', 'http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/468196/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(480, 'Popcorn Day, Ntl. (1853): January 19', 'United States', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.cretors.com/page.asp?i=12', 'Popcorn_DayF.jpg', 'Popcorn_DayE.jpg', 'About National Popcorn Day', NULL, 'National Popcorn Day marks the anniversary of the birth of Charles Cretors on January 19, 1853. \n\nCretors owned a confectionary shop in Decatur, Illinois and decided to expand his offerings out onto the sidewalk where people were. He purchased a peanut roaster, but found it lacked functionality. Tinkering, he improved it and added other products. He is the person that created the sidewalk roasters used for peanuts, coffee and popcorn that were commonplace in the late 19th century through WWII. \n\nIt is because of Cretors that you were able to go to the boardwalk, ball game or circus and enjoy roasted peanuts or popcorn, fresh and hot. National Popcorn Day honors his memory.\n\nPopcorn has been around for about 4,000 years, but it wasn’t until 1519 that Europeans would discover it. Cortes got his first sight of popcorn when he invaded Mexico and came into contact with the Aztecs. Popcorn was an important food for the Aztec Indians, who also used popcorn as decoration for ceremonial headdresses, necklaces and ornaments on statues of their gods, including Tlaloc, the god of rain and fertility.\n\nToday it is a favorite snack the world over. Americans consume some 16 billion quarts a year, or 51 quarts per man, woman, and child.\n\nThe Popcorn Board is the official representative of all things popcorn in the United States. They have over 50 recipes you can download with pictures on their site at: \n\nhttp://www.popcorn.org/AboutUs/Media/PopcornPhotos/tabid/112/Default.aspx\n\nNot all corn kernels pop. Only the Zea mays everta corn can become popcorn.\n', 'Historical Anniversary. No Sponsor. See The Popcorn Board for ideas', 'The Popcorn Board', '330 North Wabash Avenue, Suite 2000 ', 'Chicago', 'IL', 'US', '60611', '(312) 644.6610', 'info@popcorn.org', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.popcorn.org/AboutUs/ContactUs/tabid/111/Default.aspx', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"480\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/6W15yeJkOK8\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"480\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/My7Ilcb0sGA\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/zOm3vHuygQg\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
(481, 'Poverty Eradication, 3rd Intl. Decade: 2018 - 2027', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2018', '2018-01-01', '12', '31', '2027', '2027-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '59', '18', '8', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Decade', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://www.un.org/development/desa/socialperspectiveondevelopment/issues/poverty-eradication.html', NULL, NULL, 'About the 3rd International Decade for the Eradication of Poverty', NULL, 'Hunger, malnutrition, lack of education, lack of opportunity, poor health, discrimination, these are just some of the results and stigma associated with poverty. If you\'ve ever experienced a period of time in your own life when you weren\'t sure where the money was going to come from to pay the rent, buy food or medicine, where you couldn\'t travel to visit family or had to drop out of school because you couldn\'t come up with tuition, you\'ve had a taste of what millions of people live with every day. You know the fear, the all-consuming anxiety and the hopelessness that comes with it. The United Nations continues to address all perspectives of poverty globally and has continued its decade into a third term until poverty becomes a thing of the past. ', 'United Nations', 'Department of Public Information', ' ', 'New York City', 'NY', 'US', '10017', '(212) 963.7160', 'malu@un.org', 'Media Liaison', 'http://www.un.org/en/media/accreditation/contact.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:50', '2021-03-01 04:20:50'),
