(547, 'Snowmobile Safety & Awareness Week: January 18-26', 'Worldwide', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '42', '45', '47', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'www.snowmobile.org', NULL, NULL, 'About International Snowmobile Safety & Awareness Week', NULL, 'Snowmobile Safety & Awareness Week is dedicated to raising awareness about snowmobile safety.\n\nPromoted by the International Snowmobile Manufacturers Association (ISMA), there are over 1.2 million registered snowmobiles in the United States alone; snowmobile safety is a serious issue.', 'International Snowmobile Manufacturers Association (ISMA)', '1640 Haslett Road, Suite 170', NULL, 'Haslett', 'MI', 'US', '48840', '(517) 339.7788 ', 'ismasue@aol.com', 'General Information', 'http://www.snowmobile.org/contact-isma.aspx', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PNXitKHRB-Y\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(548, 'Social Security Check Day (1940): January 31', 'United States', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '18', '60', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.ssa.gov/history/imf.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Social Security Check Day', NULL, 'Social Security Check Day marks the anniversary of the first Social Security check issued in the United States on January 31, 1940 to Ida May Fuller in the amount of $22.54. Its number, 00-000-001, reflected this. \n\nMiss Fuller had filed her retirement claim on November 4 the previous year, having worked under Social Security for almost three years. \n\nEver since, Social Security has been a vital part of the United States\' retirement program for senior citizens and the disabled.', 'Historic Anniversary. See the Social Security Administration for history. ', 'Social Security Administration', '2100 M St NW', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20037', '(866) 752.0634 x 17518', 'Tanya.Fairell.Johnson@ssa.gov', 'Tanya Fairell Johnson, Public Affairs', 'https://www.ssa.gov/phila/pub_aff.htm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(549, 'Someday We\'ll Laugh About this Week: January 2-8', 'Worldwide', '1', '2', '2020', '2020-01-02', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '26', '17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Weekly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.humorproject.com', NULL, NULL, 'About Someday We\'ll Laugh About This Week', NULL, 'A reminder of the healing power of laughter and the need not to take life too seriously.  Someday We\'ll Laugh About This is a universal statement of coping. Why wait? Laugh today.\n\nThis event began in 1977.', 'The Humor Project', '10 Madison Ave. ', NULL, 'Saratoga Springs', 'NY', 'US', '12866', '(518) 587.8770', 'chase@humorproject.com', 'Dr. Joel Goodman', 'http://www.humorproject.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(550, 'Soup Month, Ntl.: January ', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.campbells.com/kitchen/recipe-collections/its-national-soup-month/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Soup Month', NULL, 'January is the National Soup Month in the United States. \n\nSoups have been an essential component of cuisine for centuries in every culture. Cold or hot, spicy or not, sweet or salty, soups are versatile, economical, hearty and healthy.\n\nThis is an unofficial event with no sponsor.  ', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor. See Campbell\'s on topic. ', 'Campbell Soup Company', ' 1 Campbell Place', 'Camden', 'NJ', 'US', ' 08103-1701', '(800) 257.8443', 'media@campbellsoup.com', 'Media Relations', 'https://www.campbellsoupcompany.com/newsroom/media-contact/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(551, 'Spaghetti Day, Ntl.: January 4', 'United States', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.foodnetwork.com/healthyeats/recipes/2012/01/happy-national-spaghetti-day', NULL, NULL, 'About National Spaghetti Day', NULL, 'National Spaghetti Day celebrates the round wheat noodle covered in sauce known as spaghetti. The dish originated in Italy and on the island of Sicilia. \n\nThe first possible mention of a Spaghetti type dish occurs in the 12th Century book by Abu Abdullah Mohammed al Idrisi, \'The Book of Roger\'. In it he details the culture and cuisine in various areas of the Mediterranean, most notably in the town of Trabia on the island of Sicily. Here, using hard wheat, the natives made a dough in long strands that they then exported to other areas.  The book was written nearly a century prior to Marco Polo’s exhibitions to the Far East. It is believed this first form of spaghetti could have been what we refer to as vermicelli today.  In Italian, that word means ‘thin worms’ in Italian. Either way, today is the day to celebrate spaghetti, with or without marinara sauce.  Enjoy!\n\nTo read more about the Sicilian origin of Spaghetti and the pasta of its name see: http://www.bestofsicily.com/mag/art73.htm', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(552, 'Spouse\'s Day: January 26', 'United States', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '40', '26', '17', '29', '52', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9OGqYSnSftg', NULL, NULL, 'About National Spouse\'s Day', NULL, 'Spouse\'s Day in the United States is set aside to show gratitude and appreciation for the man or woman who stands beside you through thick and thin.', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(553, 'Spring Festival Holiday (CN): January 24-30', 'China', '1', '24', '2020', '2020-01-24', '1', '30', '2020', '2020-01-30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '15', '17', '61', '69', NULL, 'Weekly', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.travelchinaguide.com/essential/holidays/spring-festival.htm', 'Spring_FestivalF.jpg', 'Spring_FestivalE.jpg', 'About China\'s Spring Festival', NULL, 'The Spring Festival is the name given to the 15 day period between the Chinese New Year and the Festival of Lanterns. This is a big holiday in China and with Chinese communities worldwide. It is treated much like Christmas in the West or the Eid Holidays in the Islamic world. A national holiday, the entire country takes a week off for the celebrations.\n\nGifts are exchanged and red packets with money in even number denominations. Families travel far and wide to be together, special foods are prepared with the night before the Chinese New Year called the ‘reunion dinner’ being the most important.  And  of course, the  retailers have many specials leading up to and during the festivities.  Activities culminate on the 15th day with the Lantern Festival, marking the end of the annual Chinese New Year Celebration. For any business doing business with China, basically lock out the week leading up to it and the first seven days of the fifteen day period. You’ll have a hard time getting anyone to pay much attention to business. This time is about celebrating. \n\nEach day of the Spring Festival has a different activity.\n\nDay 1: Welcoming of the deities with firecrackers, dragon dancing and a vegetarian diet.\n\nDay 2: Married daughters visit their parents\n\nDay 3: Red Mouth Day is used to burn paper as a sign of destroying wrath. It is considered very unlucky to visit or have guests on this day.\n\nDay 4: Dinner hosted by companies and employers. Businesses go back to work. \n\nDay 5: Birthday of the god of Wealth. Firecrackers are shot to insure his favor, good fortune and prosperity in the year ahead.\n\nDay 6: open\n\nDay 7: Everyone becomes one year older, regardless of their actual birthday. Buddhists will avoid meet and others will have a raw fish salad to eat in order to promote wealth and prosperity in the year ahead. \n\nDay 8: Family dinner night, company hosted lunch or dinner, all to celebrate the birth of the Jade emperor. In the hours leading up to midnight, incense are burnt and food offerings are made. Should a family fail to make offerings, the Kitchen god reports their lack of adherence to the Jade Emperor. \n\nDay 9: A Day of Prayers  and offerings to the Jade Emperor.\n\nDay 10: A party is held for the Jade Emperor.\n\nDay 11 & 12: Celebrations and parties continue with lots of food.\n\nDay 13: Vegetarian day to cleanse the stomach and prayers, offerings and various forms of honor are paid to the Chinese god of War, General Guan Yu from the Han dynasty.\n\nDay 14: Open\n\nDay 15: The Shangyuan Festival of lanterns is when people eat traditional Chinese foods like rice dumplings, rice ball soup and candies. Families walk the streets together with colorful lanterns.', 'National Festival. See China National Tourism Administration for info', 'China National Tourism Administration', '9A Jianguomennei Ave', 'Beijing', NULL, 'CN', '100740', '(+86) 10 65.20.1114', 'webmaster@cnta.gov.cn ', 'Media Relations', 'http://en.cnta.gov.c bout/Forms/AboutCnta/ContactUs.shtml', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(554, 'Squirrel Day: January 21', 'United States', '1', '21', '2020', '2020-01-21', '1', '21', '2020', '2020-01-21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'www.wildwnc.org', NULL, NULL, 'About National Squirrel Day', NULL, 'Squirrel Day or Squirrel Appreciation Day is a to express our love for the little, nut-eating rascals that are squirrels.  Squirrels are an essential part of the ecosystem and provide hours of joy to those lucky enough to watch them go about their day. \n\nThis event was created in 2001 by Christy Hargrove of the Wild North Carolina Nature Center.', 'Wild North Carolina Nature Center', '75 Gashes Creek Rd', NULL, 'Asheville', 'NC', 'US', '28815', '(828) 259.8092', 'https://wildwnc.org/contact', 'Media Relations', 'https://wildwnc.org/contact', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(555, 'Stalking Awareness Month, Ntl.: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '42', '26', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.stalkingawarenessmonth.org', NULL, NULL, 'About National Stalking Awareness Month', NULL, 'National Stalking Awareness Month in the United States aims to raise awareness of stalking. \n\nStalking is a serious social issue that happens more often than most realize. \nThe majority of stalking victims keep it to themselves or fail to realize it is happening. Stalking can, and often does, lead to rape, murder, blackmail and theft. Stalking Awareness Month reminds people of the problem and to urges them educate themselves, learning the warning signs and take appropriate precautions.', 'National Center for Victims of Crime', '2000 M Street NW, Suite 480', NULL, 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20036', '(202) 467.8700', ' ', 'General Information', ' http://victimsofcrime.org/top-links/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(556, 'Static Electricity Day: January 9', 'United States', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', '1', '9', '2020', '2020-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '43', '46', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.sciencemadesimple.com/static.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Static Electricity Day', NULL, 'Static Electricity Day celebrates the oft amusing and somewhat annoying physical effect of static electricity. \n\nWhether you\'ve zapped your hand on a doorknob, or you\'ve had your hair go in every direction in an instant after removing a scarf or a hat, we\'ve all experienced this interesting phenomenon. \n\nCheck Science Made Simple\'s article on static electricity to see how exactly this works and why it happens: \n\nhttp://www.sciencemadesimple.com/static.html', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(557, 'Stephen Foster Day (1864): January 13', 'United States', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '32', '12', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Foster', NULL, NULL, 'About National Stephen Foster Day', NULL, 'Stephen Foster Day is a historic anniversary marking his death January 13, 1864. \n\nBorn in July 4, 1826, Stephen Foster is an American songwriter, known as \'the father of American music. Foster wrote over 200 parlor and minstrel songs, including \'Oh! Susana\', \'Camptown Races\', \'Old Folks at Home\', \'My Old Kentucky Home\', \'Jeanie with the Light Brown Hair\', \'Old Black Joe\', and \'Beautiful Dreamer\'. \n\nHis work continues to live on as a part of childhood and the American experience.', 'Historic Anniversary. No Sponsor. ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(558, 'Sticker Day, Ntl (1907): January 13', 'United States', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '22', '12', '18', '39', '52', 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.stickergiant.com/national-sticker-day', NULL, NULL, 'About National Sticker Day', NULL, 'Today is the birthday of Ray Stanton Avery, January 13, 1907. Avery invented the first self adhesive labels for pricing, known as the Kum Kleen Pricer Stickers. This single invention grew into the company we know today as Avery Dennison Corporation. From the humble price sticker grew an entire industry of commercial and copyrighted colorful stickers, ranging from gold stars and smiley faces to well known cartoons and characters. National Sticker Day celebrates the contributions of Avery to commerce and popular culture and occurs annually on the day of his birth. Avery died December 12, 1997. ', 'Historical Anniversary. See Avery Dennison on Topic.', 'Avery Dennison', '207 Goode Ave', 'Glendale', 'CA', 'US', NULL, '(626) 304.2000', NULL, 'Media Relations', 'https://www.averydennison.com/en/home/newsroom.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
