(578, 'The God Who Speaks, A Year of the Word (C)(UK): 2020', 'United Kingdom', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '12', '31', '2020', '2020-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10', '38', '49', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Annual', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://catholicnews.org.uk/Home/Special-Events/The-God-Who-Speaks/2020-A-Year-of-the-Word', NULL, NULL, 'About The God Who Speaks, 2020 A Year of the Word ', NULL, 'The Catholic Bishops’ Conference of England and Wales has announced that 2020 will be \'A Year of the World-The God Who Speaks. It is the 10th anniversary of Verbum Domini - Pope Benedict XVI’s Apostolic Exhortation on ‘The Word of the Lord’ and the 1,600 anniversary of St Jerome’s death.\n\nThroughout the year the church community will be celebrating, living and sharing God‘s word with an exciting new initiative through a range of events, activities and resources to participate in all around the country.', 'Catholic Bishops’ Conference of England and Wales', '39 Eccleston Square ', NULL, 'London', NULL, 'UK', 'SW1V 1BX', '(+44) (0)20.7901.4800', 'ccn@cbcew.org.uk', 'Media Relations', 'http://catholicnews.org.uk/Governance-and-Contact/Contact-Us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(579, 'Thesaurus Day (1779): January 18', 'United States', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '13', '58', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.thesaurus.com/', NULL, NULL, 'About Thesaurus Day', NULL, 'Thesaurus Day in the United States celebrates the writer’s resource and invaluable tool of poets, the Thesaurus. It occurs on the birthday of its creator in the English language, Peter Mark Roget (January 18, 1779 - September 12, 1869).\n\nRoget created the first modern day thesaurus in 1805, but it wasn’t published until 1852. His book, with updates, is still in print today.', 'Historical Anniversary.  No Sponsor.  ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(580, 'Thomas Crapper Day (1910): January 27', 'United States', '1', '27', '2020', '2020-01-27', '1', '27', '2020', '2020-01-27', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '43', '46', '37', '20', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.uh.edu/engines/epi157.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Thomas Crapper Day', NULL, 'Thomas Crapper Day honors Thomas Crapper an English plumber born in Yorkshire in 1837, who died on this day in 1910. \n\nThough he is often credited with inventing the modern flushing toilet, he actually improved upon it and developed a number of other inventions that contributed to modern sanitation. \n\nThe humble privy in our bathrooms was actually a novelty to the American soldiers returning through England after WWI.  The \'porcelain throne\' often bore the brand name ‘Crapper’, thus Thomas’ association with its invention.  Unless you’ve traveled to other parts of the world where the western toilet is often non-existent or replaced with the vile, in the floor squat pots, you’ve probably never appreciated how important Crapper’s inventions and advancements are to your health and comfort. Or what a messy and uncomfortable process doing one’s business once was and can still be in some parts of the world.\n\nToday we honor Crapper, give thanks for his inventions.', 'Historical Anniversary.  No Sponsor.  ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(581, 'Thyroid Awareness Month: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '52', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.thyroid.org/january-thyroid-awareness/', NULL, NULL, 'About Thyroid Awareness Month', NULL, 'Thyroid Awareness Month seeks to educate the public about thyroid disease and help raise money for research.\n\nMore than 12 percent of the U.S. population will develop a thyroid condition during their lifetime.\n\nAn estimated 20 million Americans have some form of thyroid disease. Up to 60 percent of those with thyroid disease are unaware of their condition.\n\nWomen are five to eight times more likely than men to have thyroid problems. One woman in eight will develop a thyroid disorder during her lifetime. Most thyroid cancers respond to treatment, although a small percentage can be very aggressive.\n\nThe causes of thyroid problems are largely unknown.\n\nUndiagnosed thyroid disease may put patients at risk for certain serious conditions, such as cardiovascular diseases, osteoporosis and infertility.\n\nPregnant women with undiagnosed or inadequately treated hypothyroidism have an increased risk of miscarriage, preterm delivery, and severe developmental problems in their children.\n\nMost thyroid diseases are life-long conditions that can be managed with medical attention.', 'American Thyroid Association', '6066 Leesburg Pike Suite 550 ', NULL, ' Falls Church', 'VA', 'US', '22041', '  ', 'thyroid@thyroid.org', 'General Information', 'https://www.thyroid.org/january-thyroid-awareness/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(582, 'Timket (C)(ET/ER): January 19', 'Ethiopia, Eritrea, Egypt', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10', '38', '64', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Can be the 19th or the 20th. 11th day of Terr in the Ethiopian calendar.', 'https://www.selamtamagazine.com/stories/celebrating-timket', NULL, NULL, 'About Timket', NULL, 'In the Coptic, Ethiopian and Eritrean churches, Timket is the Epiphany celebration marking the baptism of Jesus Christ in the Jordan River.  It is a national holiday in Ethiopia and Eritrea.', 'National Holiday Ethiopia & Eritrea. Christian Religious Observance', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(583, 'Tin Can Day (1810): January 19', 'United States', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', '1', '19', '2020', '2020-01-19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '19', '46', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://inventors.about.com/od/cstartinventions/a/tin_can.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Tin Can Day', NULL, 'Tin Can Day celebrates the invention of tin cans on this day in 1810 by British merchant Peter Durand. A major game-changer in food preservation, tin cans revolutionized the food industry. The first commercial canning factory opened in England in 1813, thanks to John Hall and Bryan Dorkin.', 'Historical Anniversary.  No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(584, 'Toad Hollow Day of Encouragement: January 26', 'United States', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', '1', '26', '2020', '2020-01-26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '17', '58', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.toadhollow.com/wine-blog/day-of-encouragement-at-toad-hollow-tasting-room', NULL, NULL, 'About the Toad Hollow Day of Encouragement', NULL, 'Toad Hollow Day of Encouragement is a day for people to reach out and make a sincere, heartfelt connection with someone else. \n\nThe name of the holiday comes from \'Toad Hollow Country School\', a story written by a girl named Eunice in the early 19th century. The story was later picked up by her college professor Ralph C. Morrison. \n\nMr. Morrison read and liked the story so much that he incorporated it into his own storytelling and thus a legend was born. Toad Hollow Day of Encouragement is inspired the story’s message of openness and connectedness with people.', 'Toad Hollow Vineyards', 'PO BOX 876', NULL, 'Healdsburg', 'CA', 'US', '95448', '(888) 862.3846', 'http://www.toadhollow.com/contact', 'General Information', 'http://www.toadhollow.com/contact', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(585, 'Toffee, English Toffee Day, Ntl.: January 8', 'United States & United Kingdom', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', '1', '8', '2020', '2020-01-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '49', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://benguinter.com/nationalenglishtoffeeday.html', NULL, NULL, 'About National English Toffee Day', NULL, 'National English Toffee Day in both the United States and the United Kingdom celebrates the sweet made from molasses, butter, sugar and almonds. The sweet rose to popularity during the 1800s and quickly became a favorite on both sides of the pond. \n\nThis is an unofficial event with no sponsor. ', 'Unofficial Event, No Sponsor', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/dL6raM6wHTE\" frameborder=\"0\" gesture=\"media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(586, 'Tom Thumb Day (1838): January 4', 'United States', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '14', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.missioncreep.com/mundie/gallery/little/little1.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Tom Thumb Day ', NULL, 'Tom Thumb Day commemorates Charles Sherwood Stratton, a boy from Bridgeport, Connecticut, born January 4, 1838. \n\nThe son of a carpenter, at the age of four Charles was only 25 inches tall and weighed a mere 15 pounds. In the beginning his father was embarrassed by his son\'s stature, but when P. T. Barnum offered a substantial stipend for the young boy to join the circus, embarrassment gave way to pride. \n\nDubbed Tom Thumb by the showman, the small boy became an overnight sensation which continues to be remembered today on Tom Thumb Day.', 'Historical Anniversary.  No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(587, 'Train Your Dog Month, Ntl.: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '42', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.trainyourdogmonth.com', NULL, NULL, 'About National Train Your Dog Month', NULL, 'Created in 2011, National Train Your Dog Month is promoted The Association of Professional Dog Trainers. This day urges dog owners to take the time and train their dogs properly for their pets safety and for the family’s enjoyment. Resources are made available throughout the month for pet parents on the event’s website. ', 'The Association of Professional Dog Trainers', ' 2365 Harrodsburg Road A325', ' ', ' Lexington', 'KY', 'US', '40504', '(864) 331.0767', 'trainyourdogmonth@apdt.com', 'General Information', 'https://apdt.com/contact/', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tV5oGo9BQn4?ecver=1\" frameborder=\"0\" gesture=\"media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UmYg3d1OHvE\" frameborder=\"0\" gesture=\"media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“415\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/B5sL1is4GGs\" frameborder=\"0\" gesture=\"media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(588, 'Travel, Shop for Travel Day, Ntl.: January 14', 'United States', '1', '14', '2020', '2020-01-14', '1', '14', '2020', '2020-01-14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '48', '46', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '2nd Tuesday January', 'https://www.skyscanner.com/tips-and-inspiration/deals/national-shop-for-travel-day-flight-deals', NULL, NULL, 'About National Shop for Travel Day', NULL, 'There is something about a new year that causes travel queries to spike in mid-January. Obviously, people are thinking about someplace other than enduring the winter doldrums. Capitalizing on this trend and mindset, National Shop for Travel Day encourages travelers and dreamers to research places to go and things to do on their next vacation. \n\nCreated inn 2018, this date seeks to promote, like a Black Friday or Green Monday, the best travel deals available, when people are most likely to be shopping them. Bon voyage!', 'Travel Tech Association', '3033 Wilson Blvd #700', NULL, 'Arlington', 'VA', 'US', '22201', '(703) 842.3754', 'sshur@traveltech.org', 'Steve Shur,\nPresident', 'https://www.traveltech.org/contact', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(589, 'Trivia Day: January 4', 'United States', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', '1', '4', '2020', '2020-01-04', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '22', '13', '58', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://users.erols.com/jbirch/rlb/memoryville.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Trivia Day', NULL, 'Trivia Day was created by Robert I Birch, of Pun Corps, a holiday inventing company that uses numerology. For instance, Trivia Day is January 4 each year the T and R of \'Trivia\' stand for the numbers 1 and 4.\n\nThe date was chosen due to numerology. It is a testament to the collectors of vast information who seem to always have something interesting to say.\n\nTrivia Day continues despite the passing of its creator in 2005. ', 'Created by Puns Corps. No Longer Sponsored. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(590, 'Twelfth Night (C): January 5', 'Worldwide', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', '1', '5', '2020', '2020-01-05', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10', '38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twelfth_Night_(holiday)', NULL, NULL, 'About the Christian Holiday of Twelfth Night', NULL, 'January 5 in Christianity is the Twelfth Night, though some denominations of Christianity mark the Twelfth Night on January 6. It is the final night of the Twelve days of Christmas and occurs on the eve of the Epiphany.', 'Christian Religious Holiday: See the Vatican for Details', 'The Holy See', NULL, 'Vatican City', NULL, 'IT', NULL, '(+39) 06.6982', 'info@news.va', 'Media Relations', 'http://www.news.va/en/source/press-office', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(591, 'Tyvendedagen (NO); St. Knut\'s Day (SE): January 13', 'Norway & Sweden', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', '1', '13', '2020', '2020-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '10', '16', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.sacred-texts.com/etc/fwe/fwe10.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Tyvendedagen in Norway, St. Knut\'s Day in Sweden', NULL, 'Tyvendedagen in Norway, St. Knut\'s Day in Sweden or Twentieth Day is the official end of the Christmas season. Christmas trees come down and are burned. Holiday décor and greetings are retired until the next year. ', 'Norwegian & Swedish Tradition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(592, 'Ukrainian Day (UA)(1918): January 22', 'Ukraine', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', '1', '22', '2020', '2020-01-22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '36', '25', '59', '66', NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.firstworldwar.com/source/ukraine_vinichenko1.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About Ukrainian Day', NULL, 'On January 22, 1918 the nation state Ukraine proclaimed its independence from Russia. Independence would last until 1921 when the Soviet Union took control of the country. In 1991 it regained its independence again. As of February 2014, the region of Crimea is under Russian occupation again. ', 'National Holiday, Ukraine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(593, 'Unchain a Dog Month: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '20', '42', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.peta.org/features/january-unchain-dog/', NULL, NULL, 'About Unchain a Dog Month', NULL, 'With temperatures dropping, animals are vulnerable to frostbite and worse. PETA created National Unchain a Dog Month to alert pet owners to the dangers of leaving their pet chained outside during the winter months. Animals need shelter, just like people. If you cannot bring your pets inside, make sure they have adequate shelter and access to food and water that isn\'t frozen. \n\nAlso, watch for stray dogs hiding under cars and cats under car hoods. Often cats will crawl into the engine of parked cars to keep warm during winter months. ', 'PETA', '501 Front St.', NULL, 'Norfolk', 'VA', 'US', '23510', '(202) 483.7382', 'https://www.peta.org/media/contact-media-department/', 'Media Relations', 'https://www.peta.org/media/contact-media-department/', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"380\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/SEIFH5iNzJk\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=\"640\" height=\"380\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-LReX2sqTvc\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/official.peta/', 'https://twitter.com/peta/', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/officialpeta', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(594, 'Up Helly AA (UK): January 28', 'United Kingdom', '1', '28', '2020', '2020-01-28', '1', '28', '2020', '2020-01-28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '12', '48', '35', '69', '49', NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', 'Last Tuesday Jan', 'https://www.shetland.org', NULL, NULL, 'About the Scottish Festival of Up Helly Aa', NULL, 'For all you Viking fans, the town of Lerwick, Scotland has an annual celebration to close out the Yule season you\'ll love: Up Helly Aa\n\nUp Helly Aa centers on the burning of a Viking Galley each year. In Nordic culture, this was done annually as a sacrifice to the sun god. It\'s both a festival and an impressive bon fire, the likes you\'ll never see again...until the next Yuletide that is. \n\nHeld annually on the last Tuesday in January. ', 'City of Lerwick, Scotland', 'Market Cross', NULL, 'Lerwick', 'Scotland', 'UK', 'ZE1 0LU', '(+44) 15.95.69.3434', 'Lerwick.Information@visitscotland.com', 'General Information', 'https://www.visitscotland.com/info/services/lerwick-icentre-p333461', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(595, 'Use Your Gift Card Day, Ntl.: January 18', 'United States', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', '1', '18', '2020', '2020-01-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '18', '39', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '3rd Saturday January', 'https://useyourgiftcard.com', NULL, NULL, 'About Use Your Gift Card Day', NULL, 'First held in 2020, National Use Your Gift Card Day encourages people who received gift cards over the holidays and previous, to get out and redeem the full amount. Each year over $500 million dollars in gift card expenditure go unused. That is 2% of the nearly $26 billion spent on gift cards each year. Put that money where it belongs: in your gift rather than the issuers pocket. Redeem!', 'Tilson Public Relations', '1001 Yamato Rd., Ste. 300', NULL, 'Boca Raton', 'FL', 'US', '33431', '(561) 998.1995', 'info@useyourgiftcard.com', 'Tracy Tilson', 'https://useyourgiftcard.com/press/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(596, 'Vasant Panchami (H): January 29', 'Worldwide', '1', '29', '2020', '2020-01-29', '1', '29', '2020', '2020-01-29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '38', '15', '69', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://hinduism.about.com/od/festivalsholidays/p/vasantpanchami.htm', '6839_Vasant_PanchamiF.png', '6839_Vasant_PanchamiE.png', 'About Vasant Panchami Hindu Festival', NULL, 'Vasant Panchami, Saraswati Puja or the Basant Festival of Kites marks the beginning of Holi, the holy season for both Sikh and Hindu faiths.  The signature color of this event is yellow, and it is one of two spring festivals in the Hindu faith.  This festival pays tribute to Maa Saraswati, the goddess of learning, wisdom, knowledge, fine arts, refinement, science and technology and occurs 40 days prior to Holi.  Vasant Panchami is a popular celebration for tourists with its animated display of children flying kites.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: \n\nWe use the Indian Civil Calendar, which is the official holiday calendar in India, the largest Hindu nation.  The Hindu faith has many calendars, each specific to different regions and tribes with dates and celebrations marked by differing positions of the sun, moon and stars. Names of months and holidays, as well as the corresponding dates in the Gregorian Calendar, vary widely from one calendar to the next. Use our dates as a baseline. Find out which of the dozens of Hindu calendars is used in the region you live or plan to visit if you are looking to attend or witness a specific observance. ', 'Hindu Religious Holiday. See The Hindu Temple Society of North America for more information', 'New York Ganesh Temple', ' 45-57 Bowne Street', ' Flushing', 'NY', 'US', '11355', '(718) 460.8484', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', 'Media Relations', 'https://nyganeshtemple.org/', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“480\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/frTchmBy-YM\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“480\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/eQVn6-1ajck\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<iframe width=“640\" height=“360\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/ZEABcYRyWB0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(597, 'Veganuary (US/UK/AU): January', 'United States, United Kingdom, Australia', '1', '1', '2020', '2020-01-01', '1', '31', '2020', '2020-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '19', '26', '20', '4', '49', '52', 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://veganuary.com', NULL, NULL, 'About Veganuary', NULL, 'Veganuary is a charity inspiring people to try vegan for January and throughout the rest of the year in the United Kingdom.  Recipes and activities are available on the event\'s website. This event first ran in 2014.\n\nWhat does it mean to go vegan? Vegan is not vegetarian, which simply means you do not eat meat. Vegans refrain from eating, using or enjoying any of the following:\n\n1) No Meat, dairy, fish, or eggs.\n\n2) No clothing made from animals including leather, fur, wool, or silk.\n\n3) No products tested on animals.\n\n4) No attending or watching entertainment that uses animals including film, TV, circuses, zoos, rodeos, hunting, and wild animal parks.', 'Veganuary', 'PO Box 719', NULL, 'York', NULL, 'UK', 'YO1 0HF', NULL, 'https://veganuary.com/contact/', 'General Information', 'https://veganuary.com/contact/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51'),
(598, 'Vision Board Day, Ntl.: January 11', 'United States', '1', '11', '2020', '2020-01-11', '1', '11', '2020', '2020-01-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '8', '20', '22', '52', ' ', NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', '2nd Saturday January', 'https://www.facebook.com/KellanLutz', NULL, NULL, 'About Vision Board Day', NULL, 'Vision Boards are a pictorial representation of goals. Vision Board Day encourages everyone to define their goals for the upcoming year and create a visual reminder of these goals you can see. Vision boards can be done with cutting and pasting from magazines and pictures, or virtually done on websites and social media. This event was first held in 2016 and created by actor Kellan Lutz and manager Ryan Daly. ', 'Kellan Lutz, Ryan Daly', NULL, NULL, 'Los Angeles', 'CA', 'US', NULL, NULL, 'Twitter: @KellanLutz', 'Kellan Lutz', 'https://www.facebook.com/KellanLutz', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-03-01 04:20:51', '2021-03-01 04:20:51');
