(650, 'Argyle Day: January 8', 'United States', '1', '8', '2021', '2021-01-08', '1', '8', '2021', '2021-01-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '39', '49', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.washingtonpost.com/posteverything/wp/2015/03/18/argyle-isnt-the-preppy-staple-you-think-it-is-thats-why-its-the-best/', NULL, NULL, 'About Argyle Day', NULL, 'Created in 2009, Argyle Day attempts to brighten up the winter by encouraging everyone to wear something argyle on this day. Argyle is the pattern used by the Campbell Clan, which originated in Argyll in western Scotland, beginning in the 17th Century. It was a sign of rebellion in thread that virtually means: anti-establishment, with regard to the crown. Today it is often associated with the Windsor\'s or preppies, but it\'s Campbell and rebel through and through.\n\nThe pattern is diamonds upon diamonds, the shape that is, and can be in a variety of color combinations. ', 'Keely McAleer', '515 N 162nd Ave. Ste. 202', NULL, 'Omaha', 'NE', 'US', '68118', '(402) 334.8899', 'kmcaleer@mheginc.com', 'Keely McAleer', 'Traditional Source', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
