(823, 'Holy Year, Jubilee (C)(ES): 2021', 'Worldwide', '1', '1', '2021', '2021-01-01', '12', '31', '2021', '2021-12-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10', '48', '16', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Annual', 'Changes', 'Years when 7/25 is a Sunday. Next is 2027.', 'https://oficinadelperegrino.com/en/pilgrimage/holy-year/', 'HolyYearF.png', 'HolyYearE.png', 'About the Holy Year and Jubilee', NULL, 'When the Feast of St. James (July 25) falls on a Sunday, that year is celebrated as a Holy Year and a year of Jubilee. The custom began with a Papel Bull issued by Pope Alexander III in 1179. It is believed in Roman Catholic christianity that if one visits the shrine of the apostle during this year, punishment for their sins will be cleansed. It is referred to as plenary indulgence.\n\nTherefore, in holy years, the Cathedral of Santiago sees a significant increase in religious pilgrims. They enter through the \'Holy Door\'. Access to this significant entrance is only available during Holy Years. Image: Jl FilpoC, CC BY-SA 4.0 <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0>, via Wikimedia Commons ', 'Cathedral of Santiago', '0', '15705 Santiago de Compostela', '0', NULL, 'ES', NULL, '(+34) 981.568.846', 'oficinadelperegrino@catedraldesantiago.es', 'General  Information', 'https://oficinadelperegrino.com/en/pilgrimage/holy-year/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
