(841, 'Inauguration Day: January 20', 'United States', '1', '20', '2021', '2021-01-20', '1', '20', '2021', '2021-01-20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '36', '25', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Changes', NULL, 'https://bideninaugural.org', NULL, NULL, 'About Inauguration Day in the US', NULL, 'Every four years the United States swears in its president and vice president for the next four years. In 2020 President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris will be sworn in at 12:01 PM on January 20. Mr. Biden will be the oldest person ever sworn in as President and Ms. Harris is the first woman and first person of color to hold the office of Vice President in the United States. \n\nAs the exiting president chose to break with convention, tradition and protocol, refusing to take part in the ceremony and leaving the city before the event, Vice President Pence will be representing his administration during the peaceful transfer of power. Mr. Biden will become the 46th President of the United States. Ms. Harris will become the 49th Vice President of the United States. ', 'Biden Harris Inaugural Committee', NULL, NULL, 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', NULL, NULL, 'privacy@bideninaugural.org', 'Pili Tobar', 'https://bideninaugural.org/getinvolved/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Capital Building, Washington DC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yes', 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
