(848, 'Introvert Day, World: January 2', 'Worldwide', '1', '2', '2021', '2021-01-02', '1', '2', '2021', '2021-01-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '26', '17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://introvertdear.com', NULL, NULL, 'About World Introvert Day', NULL, 'Extroverts, those people that love attention and are easy to spot in a crowd are approximately 60% of the population. Introverts tend to be quiet in crowds, and are often not seen. This allows them to see and hear a lot though. Therefore, after a month or so of socializing, family and holidays, introverts need a day to rest and recharge. Since 2011, January 2 has been set aside to celebrate these quietly powerful members of society and give them the greatest gift of all: rest and relaxation. ', 'Introvert Dear', '500 Westover Dr. #12657', NULL, 'Sanford', 'NC', 'US', '27330', NULL, 'Jenn@introvertdear.com', 'Jenn Granneman, Founder', 'https://introvertdear.com/media/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/introvertdearblog', 'https://www.tumblr.com/blog/introvertdear', 'https://twitter.com/IntrovertDear', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
