(894, 'Midwife\'s / Women\'s Day (GR): January 8', 'Greece', '1', '8', '2021', '2021-01-08', '1', '8', '2021', '2021-01-08', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '8', '17', '50', '16', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://books.google.com/books?id=L10pDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA149&lpg=PA149&dq=Midwife%27s+Day+in+greece&source=bl&ots=qh6W8ikAr_&sig=ACfU3U1yMFs61_a8xQczC2yFgzBixvbSmQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiU3MuUj9znAhWJhHIEHW-oD4UQ6AEwB3oECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=Midwife\'s%20Day%20in%20greece&f=false', NULL, NULL, 'About Midwife\'s / Women\'s Day in Greece', NULL, 'The Greeks know how to make a celebration fun. Midwife\'s or Women\'s Day in Greece is held annually. Women of childbearing age get out of the house, dine and pamper and leave caring and cleaning to men for the day. In some smaller villages, men caught outside on this day are greeted with a bucket of cold water splashed at them...and promptly told to return to the house for the rest of the day. \n\nAs most traditions, this day does have ties to the Bible. It\'s tied to Saint Agia Domnikes, the midwife who is believed to have help the Panagia with the birth of Christ, whose baptism is celebrated on Epiphany in Greece. The Day of Agia Domnikes, or Midwife\'s Day is celebrated annually two days later. The water ritual evolved from the practice of pouring out water, (in preparation for giving birth) for the selected midwife on this day by fertile women. In olden days, women kissed a sausage or leek and provided gifts for the ceremonial midwife. Today they eat the sausage, drink a lot of wine, eat and at times, douse men in cold water. What fun!', 'Greek Tradition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(895, 'Migration Week, Ntl.: January 3-9', 'United States', '1', '3', '2021', '2021-01-03', '1', '9', '2021', '2021-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '59', '36', '15', '10', '52', NULL, 'Weekly', 'changes', 'Week of Jan. 6', 'http://www.usccb.org/about/migration-and-refugee-services/national-migration-week/index.cfm', NULL, NULL, 'About National Migration Week', NULL, 'The Catholic Church in the United States will celebrates National Migration Week. It is an opportunity to reflect on the circumstances confronting migrants, including immigrants, refugees and survivors of human trafficking.  Regardless of where we are and where we came from, we remain part of the human family and are called to live in solidarity with one another. We celebrate this theme during the Share the Journey campaign, a global effort by the Church to show love to our migrant and refugee neighbors.', 'Catholic Church in the United States', 'United States Conference \nof Catholic Bishops', '3211 Fourth Street NE', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20017', '(202) 541.3000', 'media-relations@usccb.org', 'Office of Public Affairs', 'http://www.usccb.org/about/public-affairs/index.cfm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(896, 'Milk Bottle & Milkman Day, Ntl. (1878): January 11', 'United States', '1', '11', '2021', '2021-01-11', '1', '11', '2021', '2021-01-11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '46', '19', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.milkbottlecollectors.com', NULL, NULL, 'About Milk Bottle & Milkman Day ', NULL, 'National Milk Bottle & Milkman Day commemorates the first home deliveries of milk by a \'milkman\' January 11, 1878 by the New York Dairy Company. \n\nThe service no longer exists. \'Honey, can you pick up milk on your way home?\' is a familiar request in households. So familiar that supermarkets and convenience stores purposely put milk at the back of their stores hoping people will have impulse purchases as they walk through. One could argue that companies like Fresh Direct and Amazon have become the gig-economy milkmen. \n\nThis event is organized and promoted every year by the National Association of Milk Bottle Collectors (NAMBC).', 'National Association of Milk Bottle Collectors', '12808 Gran Bay Pkwy West', NULL, 'Jacksonville', 'FL', 'US', '32258', '(902) 749.2701', 'http://www.milkbottlecollectors.com/contact.html', 'General Information', 'http://www.milkbottlecollectors.com/contact.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
