(1002, 'Science Fiction Day (1920): January 2', 'Worldwide', '1', '2', '2021', '2021-01-02', '1', '2', '2021', '2021-01-02', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '58', '43', '12', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.asimovonline.com/asimov_home_page.html', NULL, NULL, 'About National Science Fiction Day', NULL, 'International Science Fiction Day is celebrated annually on January 2, the birthday of science fiction author Isaac Asimov in 1920. \n\nAn American author and professor of biochemistry at the Boston University, Asimov is best known for his works of science fiction and popular science. Asimov has multiple awards, including 2 Nebula awards and 9 Hugo awards. \n\nAlthough Asimov is far from being the first author in the genre, he is viewed by many as the father of modern science fiction through his works including: \n\nThe Foundation;\n \nI, Robot; \n\nBicentennial Man; \n\nAzazel;\n\nThe Edge of Tomorrow;\n\nThe Fantastic Voyage;\n\nand many others.', 'Historic Anniversary. See Asimov Online for information', ' Asimov Online', '12808 Gran Bay Parkway West', 'Jacksonville', 'FL', 'US', '32258', '(570) 708.8780', 'ejseiler@earthlink.net', ' Edward Seiler', ' http://www.asimovonline.com/asimov_home_page.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
