(1007, 'Self-help Group Awareness Month: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2021', '2021-01-01', '1', '31', '2021', '2021-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '20', '26', '1', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.whitesandstreatment.com/2016/01/19/january-is-self-help-group-awareness-month/', NULL, NULL, 'About National Self-help Group Awareness Month', NULL, 'Self-help Group Awareness Month in the United States kicks off the new year.\n\nAfter the exhausting winter holidays and as most people prepare their goals for the new year, Self-help Group Month encourages people who are in need of assistance to find the right group of people that will help them help themselves. Self-help groups support self-awareness, self-esteem, sobriety maintenance, and offer valuable community support to persons dealing with major life challenges, be it divorce, disease or just getting back on their feet. January is the perfect month of the year for people to start a new chapter of their lives and self-help groups can make that happen.', 'American Self-Help Clearinghouse', '375 E McFarlan St', ' ', 'Dover', 'NJ', 'US', '07801', '(973) 989.1122', 'admin@selfhelpgroups.org', 'General Information', 'https://healthfinder.gov/FindServices/Organizations/Organization.aspx?code=hr1681', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(1008, 'Sh\'vat (J): January 14 - February 12', 'Worldwide', '1', '14', '2021', '2021-01-14', '2', '12', '2021', '2021-02-12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '24', '38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Changes', NULL, 'http://www.ou.org/chagim/roshchodesh/shevat/default.htm', NULL, NULL, 'About the Jewish Month of Sh\'vat', NULL, 'All Hebrew calendar months begin and end at sundown. LEEP Calendar marks Jewish months beginning the first full day. Observant people of the faith will begin marking the month sundown the day prior. Sh\'vat or Shevat is the fifth month of the civil year and the eleventh month of the ecclesiastical year on the Hebrew calendar. \n\nThe name Shevat comes from the Akkadian language of the Babylonian Captivity of the Hebrew people. The meaning of the word in its original language is \'strike\' and refers to the heavy rains of the season.', 'Jewish Religious Calendar. See Jewish Orthodox Union for background, information.', 'Jewish Orthodox Union', '11 Broadway', 'New York', 'NY', 'US', '10004', '(212) 613.8318', 'steiners@ou.org', 'Stephen Steiner, Public Relations', 'http://www.ou.org/contact/', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
