(1021, 'Social Security Check Day (1940): January 31', 'United States', '1', '31', '2021', '2021-01-31', '1', '31', '2021', '2021-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '18', '60', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.ssa.gov/history/imf.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Social Security Check Day', NULL, 'Social Security Check Day marks the anniversary of the first Social Security check issued in the United States on January 31, 1940 to Ida May Fuller in the amount of $22.54. Its number, 00-000-001, reflected this. \n\nMiss Fuller had filed her retirement claim on November 4 the previous year, having worked under Social Security for almost three years. \n\nEver since, Social Security has been a vital part of the United States\' retirement program for senior citizens and the disabled.', 'Historic Anniversary. See the Social Security Administration for history. ', 'Social Security Administration', '2100 M St NW', 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20037', '(866) 752.0634 x 17518', 'Tanya.Fairell.Johnson@ssa.gov', 'Tanya Fairell Johnson, Public Affairs', 'https://www.ssa.gov/phila/pub_aff.htm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
