(1026, 'Squirrel Day: January 21', 'United States', '1', '21', '2021', '2021-01-21', '1', '21', '2021', '2021-01-21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'www.wildwnc.org', NULL, NULL, 'About National Squirrel Day', NULL, 'Squirrel Day or Squirrel Appreciation Day is a to express our love for the little, nut-eating rascals that are squirrels.  Squirrels are an essential part of the ecosystem and provide hours of joy to those lucky enough to watch them go about their day. \n\nThis event was created in 2001 by Christy Hargrove of the Wild North Carolina Nature Center.', 'Wild North Carolina Nature Center', '75 Gashes Creek Rd', NULL, 'Asheville', 'NC', 'US', '28815', '(828) 259.8092', 'https://wildwnc.org/contact', 'Media Relations', 'https://wildwnc.org/contact', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(1027, 'Stalking Awareness Month, Ntl.: January', 'United States', '1', '1', '2021', '2021-01-01', '1', '31', '2021', '2021-01-31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '42', '26', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monthly', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.stalkingawarenessmonth.org', NULL, NULL, 'About National Stalking Awareness Month', NULL, 'National Stalking Awareness Month in the United States aims to raise awareness of stalking. \n\nStalking is a serious social issue that happens more often than most realize. \nThe majority of stalking victims keep it to themselves or fail to realize it is happening. Stalking can, and often does, lead to rape, murder, blackmail and theft. Stalking Awareness Month reminds people of the problem and to urges them educate themselves, learning the warning signs and take appropriate precautions.', 'National Center for Victims of Crime', '2000 M Street NW, Suite 480', NULL, 'Washington', 'DC', 'US', '20036', '(202) 467.8700', ' ', 'General Information', ' http://victimsofcrime.org/top-links/contact-us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(1028, 'Static Electricity Day: January 9', 'United States', '1', '9', '2021', '2021-01-09', '1', '9', '2021', '2021-01-09', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '43', '46', '52', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.sciencemadesimple.com/static.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Static Electricity Day', NULL, 'Static Electricity Day celebrates the oft amusing and somewhat annoying physical effect of static electricity. \n\nWhether you\'ve zapped your hand on a doorknob, or you\'ve had your hair go in every direction in an instant after removing a scarf or a hat, we\'ve all experienced this interesting phenomenon. \n\nCheck Science Made Simple\'s article on static electricity to see how exactly this works and why it happens: \n\nhttp://www.sciencemadesimple.com/static.html', 'Unofficial Event. No Sponsor.', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(1029, 'Stephen Foster Day (1864): January 13', 'United States', '1', '13', '2021', '2021-01-13', '1', '13', '2021', '2021-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '32', '12', '52', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Foster', NULL, NULL, 'About National Stephen Foster Day', NULL, 'Stephen Foster Day is a historic anniversary marking his death January 13, 1864. \n\nBorn in July 4, 1826, Stephen Foster is an American songwriter, known as \'the father of American music. Foster wrote over 200 parlor and minstrel songs, including \'Oh! Susana\', \'Camptown Races\', \'Old Folks at Home\', \'My Old Kentucky Home\', \'Jeanie with the Light Brown Hair\', \'Old Black Joe\', and \'Beautiful Dreamer\'. \n\nHis work continues to live on as a part of childhood and the American experience.', 'Historic Anniversary. No Sponsor. ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
(1030, 'Sticker Day, Ntl (1907): January 13', 'United States', '1', '13', '2021', '2021-01-13', '1', '13', '2021', '2021-01-13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '22', '12', '18', '39', '52', 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'https://www.stickergiant.com/national-sticker-day', NULL, NULL, 'About National Sticker Day', NULL, 'Today is the birthday of Ray Stanton Avery, January 13, 1907. Avery invented the first self adhesive labels for pricing, known as the Kum Kleen Pricer Stickers. This single invention grew into the company we know today as Avery Dennison Corporation. From the humble price sticker grew an entire industry of commercial and copyrighted colorful stickers, ranging from gold stars and smiley faces to well known cartoons and characters. National Sticker Day celebrates the contributions of Avery to commerce and popular culture and occurs annually on the day of his birth. Avery died December 12, 1997. ', 'Historical Anniversary. See Avery Dennison on Topic.', 'Avery Dennison', '207 Goode Ave', 'Glendale', 'CA', 'US', NULL, '(626) 304.2000', NULL, 'Media Relations', 'https://www.averydennison.com/en/home/newsroom.html', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
