(1078, 'Winnie-the-Pooh Day (1882): January 18', 'Worldwide', '1', '18', '2021', '2021-01-18', '1', '18', '2021', '2021-01-18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3', '12', '9', '58', NULL, NULL, 'Daily', 'Same', NULL, 'http://www.just-pooh.com/milne.html', NULL, NULL, 'About Winnie-the-Pooh Day', NULL, 'Winnie-the-Pooh Day marks the anniversary of Alan Alexander Milne\'s birth on January 18, 1882. He first wrote of Christopher Robin (his son and one of the characters in Winnie-the-Pooh) in the poem \'Vespers\' for Vanity Fair in 1923.  \n\nThis led to his first illustrated children\'s book in 1924. This book featured a story about a Teddy Bear, but it wouldn\'t be until Christmas Eve 1925 when Winnie-the-Pooh would make his official debut in a bedtime story published in the Evening News. That bedtime story became chapter one of his 1926 book, Winnie-the-Pooh and the rest is history.\n\nHappy Winnie-the-Pooh Day!', 'Historic Anniversary. No Sponsor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LEEP', NULL, 'Pending', '2021-08-16 15:30:51', '2021-08-16 15:30:51'),
